text: For women may be exercised in teaching after that maner, as appeareth by Saint Paul Tit. ii. saying that aged wome among other vertues, must be, bene docentes, vt ad castitatem erudiant adolescentulas, well teaching, that they may enforme their yonge women to chastitie, and to loue their husbands, and to loue their children, to be cleane in countenaunce, in woordes, and in bodie, to be good huswiues benignas et subditas viris suis, boner & boughsome to their husbands.
verse_text: Who answered: The Hebrew wemem are not as the AEgyptian wemen: for they haue the knowledge to play the mindwife them selues, and before we come to them, they are deliuered.

text: As oft as you shall eate this breade, or drinke of this cuppe, you shal shewe the death of our Lorde vntill he come, and shall shewe him selfe in his glorious maiestie at the generall iudgemente, which tyme thoughe it shall be a terible and an horrible time to sinners, and to all damnable persons, yet it shal be a time of grace, of solace, and comfort to al his true & louyng seruauntes.
verse_text: Now therfore if you be readie, in what houre soeuer you shal heare the sound of the trumpet, the pipe, the harpe, of the doulcimer, and psalter, and symphonie, and of al kind of musical instruments, prostrate your selues, & adore the statua which I haue made: but if you adore not, the selfe same houre you shal be cast into the fornace of burning fyre: and what God is there that shal deliuer you out of my hand?

text: Paul: Let the same mynde be among you, that was in Christ Iesu, which whe he was in form of god, he thought it not robbery to be equal with god, but he humbleth him self, taking the forme of a seruant, made in the similitude of men, and in habite found as man, he meketh himselfe & was made obedient vnto the death, yea the death of the crosse.
verse_text: But him that was a litle lessened vnder the Angels, we see IESVS, because of the passion of death, crowned with glorie and honour: that through the grace of God he might tast death for al.

text: Genes. xxxix. my mayster hath committed and deliuered to me all that he hath in his house, so that he knoweth not what he hath in his house, no more but the meat that he ea^eth and the drinke that he drinketh when it is set afore him, there is nothing but it is vnder my hande and at my pleasure, except onelye you that are his wyfe.
verse_text: But when the yeere was ended, they came vnto him the next yeere, and sayd vnto him, We will not hide from my lord, that since our money is spent, and my lord hath the heards of the cattel, there is nothing left in the sight of my lorde, but our bodies and our ground.

text: Let euery soule submit hymself, vnto the aucthoritie of the higher powers, for there is no power, but of God, the powers that be, be ordeined of God, whosoeuer therfore resisteth the power, resisteth the ordinaunce of God, but they that resist, shal receiue to theselfes dampnacion:
verse_text: Let euery soule bee subiect vnto the higher powers: For there is no power but of God. The powers that be, are ordeined of God.

text: & led him ful boistuously, first to Annas, then to Caiphas, that was pontifexan ni illius, then to Pilate, then to Herode, because al the world should wonder on him, as condemned by so many iudges, and none of the all speaking one word for his dispatching or acquiting.
verse_text: But the next day meaning to know more diligently for what cause he was accused of the Iewes, he loosed him, and commanded the Priests to come together and al the Councel:

text: And what saith Christ of thos that offend the litle ones? He that shall offend (saith he) one off thes litle ones the which bileue in me, it were better for him that a mill stone shuld be hanged abowt his neck, and that he were drowend in the depth of the sea.
verse_text: And he that shal scandalize one of these litle ones that beleeue in me, it is expedient for him that a milstone be hanged about his neck, and that he be drowned in the depth of the sea.

text: Paul. Philip. iiij. whatsoeuer thinges are honeste, whatsoeuer thinges are pure, whatsoeuer thynges are conueniente, whatsoeuer thinges are of honest report, yf there be any vertue, yf there be anye prayse, haue you them in youre minde and do them,
verse_text: Finally, brethren, whatsoeuer things are true, whatsoeuer things are honest, whatsoeuer things are iust, whatsoeuer things are pure, whatsoeuer things are louely, whatsoeuer things are of good report: if there bee any vertue, and if there bee any praise, thinke on these things:

text: But here may be moued a question whether our sauiour hath so forbydden vs to be angry, to saye Racha, or thou foole, one to an other, that in no wise any man may so doo, but thereby he falleth in daunger of iudgement, of councell, or of hel fyre.
verse_text: Not to many people of an vnknowen tongue, or of an harde language, whose wordes thou canst not vnderstand: yet if I should sende thee to them, they would obey thee.

text: Dost thou not knowe, that ye kindnes of god doth lead the to repentaunce, but thou after thine hard heart that cannot repente, dost hepe together the treasure of wrath agaynst the day of vengeauce and reuelation of the tru iudgement of GOD.
verse_text: But thou after thyne harde herte that cannot repet heapest ye togedder the treasure of wrath agaynste the daye of vengeauce when shalbe opened the rightewes iudgement of god

text: Timo. i. The lawe is not geue vnto a ryghteous man, but vnto the vnryghteous and disobedient, to the vngodly and to synners, to vnholye and vncleane, to murtherers of fathers, and murtherers of mothers, to manslears, and hooremongers.
verse_text: Knowing this, that the Lawe is not giuen vnto a righteous man, but vnto the lawles and disobedient, to the vngodly, and to sinners, to the vnholy, and to the prophane, to murtherers of fathers and mothers, to manslayers,

text: Per quem habemus redemptionem, per sanguinem ipsius, remissione peccatorum, de qua ubertim nobis impartiuit, in omni sapientia & prudentia, patefacto nobis arcano voluntatis suae iuxta beneplacitum suum, quod proposuerat in seipso &c.
verse_text: sic et Christus semel oblatus est ad multorum exhaurienda peccata: secundo sine peccato apparebit exspectantibus se, in salutem.

text: O Ierusalem, Ierusalem, thou that kyilest the prophetes, and stonest theim whiche are sent vnto thee, howe often would I haue gathered thy children together, euen as the Henne gathereth her chickyns vnder her wynges, and ye would not?
verse_text: O Hierusalem, Hierusalem, which killest the Prophets, and stonest them that are sent vnto thee; how often would I haue gathered thy children together, as a henne doeth gather her brood vnder her wings, & ye would not?

text: let vs not be idle and slothful, but cherefullye let vs take in hand the paines of the haruest, for he that doth gather in the heruest, (saith Salomon) is a wise child, but he that is slothful in the sommer, is a childe of confusion.
verse_text: Let not the wages of any man, which hath wrought for thee, tary with thee, but giue him it out of hand: for if thou serue God he will also repay thee: be circumspect, my sonne, in all things thou doest, and be wise in all thy conuersation.

text: esurimus, sitimus, nudi sumus, colaphis cedimur, instabiles sumus, maledicimur & benedicimus, persecutionem patimur & sustinemus, blasphemamur & obsecramus, tanque purgamenta huius mundi facti sumus, omnium peripsema usque ad huc.
verse_text: Traditi enim sumus ego et populus meus, ut conteramur, jugulemur, et pereamus. Atque utinam in servos et famulas venderemur: esset tolerabile malum, et gemens tacerem: nunc autem hostis noster est, cujus crudelitas redundat in regem.

text: Peter here) that any of you shoulde suffer for manslaughter, as a murtherer, or as a thefe, or as a sclaunderer or backbiter, or blasphemer, or as one that goeth about to take awaye other mens goodes, to spoile and robbe them.
verse_text: But let none of you suffer as a murtherer, or as a theefe, or as an euill doer, or as a busibody in other mens matters.

text: Si ministratio mortis litteris deformata in lapidibus fuit in gloria, ita vt non possent intendere filij Israell in faciem Mois^ propter gloriam vultus eius que euacuatur quo modo non magis ministratio spiritus erit in gloria?
verse_text: Pater noster mortuus est in deserto, nec fuit in seditione, quae concitata est contra Dominum sub Core, sed in peccato suo mortuus est: hic non habuit mares filios. Cur tollitur nomen illius de familia sua, quia non habuit filium? date nobis possessionem inter cognatos patris nostri.

text: If thou doe thys, thou shalt be able to fulfill Gods empery and authoritie, and shalt be able to sustaine that God byddeth thee doe, and all thys people shall returne with peace to their houses or lodgynge at tyme conuenient.
verse_text: And now thou art both beautifull in thy countenance, and wittie in thy wordes; surely if thou doe as thou hast spoken, thy God shall be my God, and thou shalt dwel in the house of king Nabuchodonosor, and shalt be renowmed through the whole earth.

text: I will doe it. And also he saith: seurly I say vnto you, that all these things which you shall ask my father in my name, he will geue them you, vntill this tyme you haue asked nothing in my name, ask, and you shall receaue,
verse_text: And in that day me you shal aske any thing. Amen, amen I say to you, if you aske the Father any thing in my name, he wil giue it you.

text: Agayne Titus.iij, for we our selues also were in times past vnwyse, disobediente, deceaued, in daunger to lustes, and to dyuers maners of voluptuousnes, liuing in maliciousnes and enuie, full of hate, hating one another.
verse_text: For we oure selves also were in tymes past vnwyse disobedient deceaved in daunger to lustes and to diuers maners of volupteousnes livynge in maliciousnes and envie full of hate hatinge one another.

text: By him, with him and in him, and, to the father all mighty in the vnitie of the holy gost, be all honor and glory, affter the which wordes this doth follow, per omnia secula seculorum, to the which is answered Amen.
verse_text: If any man speake, as the words of God. If any man minister, as of the power, which God administreth. That in al things God may be honoured by IESVS Christ: to whom is glorie & empire for euer and euer. Amen.

text: Bring in (sayth he) all youre tithes into my barnes, that there maye be meate in my house, and proue me (sayeth the Lord) in these thynges, whether I shal not open vnto you, the caractes and the cloudes of the skye,
verse_text: Bring ye all the tithes into the store-house, that there may be meate in mine house, & proue me now herewith, saith the Lord of hostes, if I will not open you the windowes of heauen, and powre you out a blessing, that there shall not be roome enough to receiue it.

text: Ye haue not chosen me, but I haue chosen you, and ordayned you, to go and bryng furth fruite, and that your fruite should remayne, that whatsoeuer ye aske of ye father in my name, he may geue it you. THE EXPOSITION.
verse_text: Ye haue not chosen me, but I haue chosen you, and ordeined you, that you should goe and bring foorth fruit, and that your fruite should remaine: that whatsoeuer ye shall aske of the Father in my Name, he may giue it you.

text: And beholde a woma in the citie which was a synner, knowing that Iesus sate in y pharisees house, brought an Alabaster box of ointment & standing at his feete behinde weping, began to water hys feete wt the teares,
verse_text: And beholde a woman in that cite which was a synner assone as she knewe that. Iesus sate at meate in the pharises housse she brought an alablaster boxe of oyntment

text: And after truely truely, I say vnto you, if you eat not the flesh of the sonne of man, and drink not his bluode you shall not haue lyfe in you, he that eateth my flesh and drinketh my bloud hath lyfe euerlastinge.
verse_text: Amen, amen I say to you, Vnles you eate the flesh of the Sonne of man, and drinke his bloud, you shal not haue life in you.

text: Dathan, and Abiron, for making rebellion against Moises, and Aaron, were swalowed vp in to the earth aliue, and most terribly perished, that the rest myght by their example, feare at any time to attempt the like.
verse_text: And burie me decently, and thy mother with me, but tarie no longer at Nineue. Remember, my sonne, how Aman handled Achiacharus þ brought him vp, how out of light he brought him into darkenes, and how he rewarded him againe: yet Ahiacharus was saued, but the other had his reward, for hee went downe into darkenesse. Manasses gaue almes, and escaped the snares of death which they had set for him: but Aman fell into the snare and perished.

text: Bryng in sayth he, all your tythes into my barnes, that there maye be meate in my house, and proue me sayth the Lorde in these thynges, whether I shal not open vnto you, the caractes and the cloudes of the skye,
verse_text: Bring all the tithes into the storehouse, that there may be meat in my house, and try me in this, saith the Lord: if I open not unto you the flood-gates of heaven, and pour you out a blessing even to abundance.

text: his rule is thys. We haue (sayth he) A ryght sure word of prophecie, wherevnto yf ye take *, as vnto a light yt shineth in a darke place, you doo wel vntil the day dawne, and the daye starre arise in your harts.
verse_text: We have also a right sure worde of prophesye wher vnto yf ye take hede as vnto a lyght that shyneth in a darke place ye do wel vntill the daye dawne and the daye starre aryse in youre hertes.

text: and sayth. Euery one that forsaketh house, or brethren or systers, or father or mother, or wyfe or children, or landes for my names sake, shal receiue an hundreth folde, and the inheritance of euerlastyng life.
verse_text: And euery one that hath left house, or brethren, or sisters, or father, or mother, or wife, or children, or landes for my names sake: shal receaue an hundred-fold, & shal possesse life euerlasting.

text: O Timothie, kepe sure that, whiche is committed to thy custody, and auoide newe fangled termes, and bosting of science, falsely so called, which science whyle some dyd professe, they haue erred from the fayth.
verse_text: O Timotheus, keepe that which is committed vnto thee, and auoide prophane and vaine babblings, and oppositios of science falsely so called,

text: The woman therefore saw that the tree was good to eate of, and beautifull to the eye, and pleasaunte to beholde, and she tooke of the fruite thereof and d d eate, and gaue part to her husbade, who also did *.
verse_text: So the woman (seeing that the tree was good for meate, and that it was pleasant to the eyes, and a tree to be desired to get knowledge) tooke of the fruite thereof, and did eate, and gaue also to her husband with her, and he did eate.

text: And agreable herevnto S. Luke in the second chap. of hys sayd Gospel sayeth. * postqua ** dies octo ut circucideret *, puer, uocatum est nomen cius Iesus, quod * est ab angelo priusquam in utero conciperetur.
verse_text: sed hoc respondit: Ecce concipies et paries filium: cave ne vinum bibas, nec siceram, et ne aliquo vescaris immundo: erit enim puer nazaraeus Dei ab infantia sua, ex utero matris suae usque ad diem mortis suae.

text: It foloweth in the text Scientes quod non corruptibilibus auro vel argento redempti estis de vana vestra conuersatione paterne traditionis sed precioso sanguine quasi agni incontaminati & immaculati Christi.
verse_text: manifestati quod epistola estis Christi, ministrata a nobis, et scripta non atramento, sed Spiritu Dei vivi: non in tabulis lapideis, sed in tabulis cordis carnalibus.

text: And yet not satisfyed with al this, he placed man in Paradyse, that is in a most pleasaunt garden, where he had planted all kynd of frute, beautifull to beholde, and delicious to eate, for man to fede vpon;
verse_text: For the which thinges thou didst nourish thy people with the meate of Angels, and bread prepared, thou gauest them from heauen without labour, hauing in it al delectation, and the sweetnes of al taste.

text: My talke, & my preaching was not in ye persuasible woordes of mans wysedome, but in shewynge of power, and of the spyryte, that youre faythe should not rest in the wisedome of man, but in the power of God.
verse_text: And my wordes and my preachinge were not with entysynge wordes of manes wysdome: but in shewinge of the sprete and of power

text: For their perdition shall ryse quickly. Saint Paul likwise Whosoeuer sayth he resisteth the hyer powers resisteth gods ordination, and they which shall resist that, shall receiue to theym selues iudgement.
verse_text: Whosoever therfore resysteth power resisteth the ordinaunce of God. And they that resist shall receave to the selfe damnacion.

text: P A G Exiij IN the sixt moneth was sent the angel Gabriel of God into a citie of Galilee named Nazareth to a virgine spoused to a man whose name was Ioseph of Dauids house and the virgines name was Mary.
verse_text: To a virgin affianced to a man whose name was Ioseph, of the house of Dauid, and the virgins name was Marie.

text: Furthermore he that shall rebuke another man, ought not onely to recite to his rebuke, what he had done vnrightfully, but he must also shewe what he hath done honestly, vertuously, and also profitably:
verse_text: if he rise, and walke abrode vpon his state, he that did strike shal be quitte, yet so that he make restitution for his worke, and for his expenses vpon the phisicians.

text: Serui obedite dominis vestris cu timore et tremore in simplicitate cordis vestri, sicut christo, non ad oculum seruientes quasi hominibus placetes, sed vt serui christi facientes voluntate dei exanimo.
verse_text: Servi, obedite per omnia dominis carnalibus, non ad oculum servientes, quasi hominibus placentes, sed in simplicitate cordis, timentes Deum.

text: Infirmatur inter vos aliquis, accersat presbiteros ecclesie & orent super eu vngetes eu oleo in nomine dni & oratio fidei saluabit infirmu et alleuiabit eu dominus et si in peccatis sic remittentur ei.
verse_text: Omnem quoque adipem auferens, sicut auferri solet adeps arietis, qui immolatur pro pacificis, cremabit super altare in incensum Domini: rogabitque pro eo, et pro peccato ejus, et dimittetur ei.

text: Then thou shalt make him king ouer the, whome the Lorde thy God shall chose. One of thy brethren must thou make Kynge ouer the, and maiest not set a straunger ouer the, whiche is not of thy brethren.
verse_text: Thou shalt in any wise set him King ouer thee, whom the Lord thy God shall choose. One from among thy brethren shalt thou set King ouer thee: thou mayest not set a stranger ouer thee, which is not thy brother.

text: But he denyed not to gyue it to such as desired it not, for he sayth, he that wyll be the greatest amongst you, must be seruaunt to the residue, by the which he sheweth both a superitorytie to be,

verse_text: For as the raine commeth down, and the snow from heauen, and returneth not thither, but watereth the earth, and maketh it bring foorth and bud, that it may giue seed to the sower, and bread to the eater:

text: Mulieres viris suis subditae sint, sicut domino, quoniam vircaput est mulieris, sicut christus caput est ecclesiae Sicut igitur ecclesia subiecta est christo, ita & mulieres virissuis in omnibus.
verse_text: quoniam vir caput est mulieris, sicut Christus caput est Ecclesiae: ipse, salvator corporis ejus.

verse_text: And Ioses, who by the Apostles was surnamed Barnabas (which is, being interpreted, The sonne of consolation) a Leuite, and of the Countrey of Cyprus,

text: sayinge: Iesus dyd call together the twelue disciples, and gaue to them power ouer vncleane spirites, that they shoulde cast them out, and shoulde heale all maner of diseases, and infirmities.
verse_text: And when hee had called vnto him his twelue disciples, he gaue them power against vncleane spirits, to cast them out, and to heale all maner of sickenesse, and all maner of disease.

text: Hebr. xiii. Obedite prepositis vestris & subiacete eis ipsi enim peruigilant quasi rationem pro animabus vestris reddituri, vt cum gaudio hoc faciant & non gementes hoc enim non expedit vobis.
verse_text: Et nunc fratres, quoniam vos estis presbyteri in populo Dei, et ex vobis pendet anima illorum, ad eloquium vestrum corda eorum erigite, ut memores sint quia tentati sunt patres nostri, ut probarentur si vere colerent Deum suum.

text: My kyngdom is not of this world, if my kyngdome were of this worlde, then would my ministers surely fight, that I should not be deliuered to ye Iewes, but nowe is my kyngdome not from hence.
verse_text: Iesus answered: my kyngdome is not of this worlde. Yf my kyngdome were of this worlde then wolde my ministres suerly fight that I shuld not be delyvered to the Iewes but now is my kyngdome not from hence.

text: Thirdly, we be taught by this gospell, that for asmuch as Marye did with a good zeale of minde, shewe vnto her sonne, that they had no wine, and neuerthelesse had but a sharpe auswere again,
verse_text: Heereupon Simon, albeit he perceiued that they spake deceiptfully vnto him, yet sent he the money, and the children, lest peraduenture he should procure to himselfe great hatred of the people:

text: Dixistis nos percussimus fedus cum morte & cum inferno fecimus pactum flagellum inundans cum transierit non veniet super nos quia posuimus mendacium, spem nostram & mendatio protecti sumus.
verse_text: Peccare et mentiri contra Dominum, et aversi sumus ne iremus post tergum Dei nostri, ut loqueremur calumniam et transgressionem; concepimus et locuti sumus de corde verba mendacii.

text: Drinke all of thys, for thys is my bloude, whiche is the newe testamente that is shed for manie, for the remission of synnes, and saint Marke sayth, they al dranke of it meaninge the cup.
verse_text: For this is my bloude of the new testament that shalbe shedde for many for the remission of synnes.

text: Ionae. i. Take me (sayth this blessed prophet) and cast me into the sea, and the sea will ceasse his rage, for I knowe that thys great tempest and storme lieth so sore on you for my sake.
verse_text: And when the King of Israel had read the letter, he rent his clothes, and sayde, Am I God, to kill and to giue life, that hee doth send to mee, that I should heale a man from his leprosie? wherfore consider, I pray you, and see howe he seeketh a quarel against me.

text: An yll tongue is a fire that marreth all and burneth vp, cosumeth, and wasteth al goodnes, specially when the fire of hell hath set it on a flame, when the deuyll hath blowen the coale.
verse_text: And the tongue is a fire, a world of iniquitie: so is the tongue amongst our members, that it defileth the whole body, and setteth on fire the course of nature, and it is set on fire of hell.

text: If you were of this world, the world woulde loue that whiche is his owne, but bicause you are not of the world, but I haue chosen you out of the worlde, therfore the worlde hateth you.
verse_text: If you hade been of the world, the world would loue his owne. But because you are not of the world, but I haue chosen you out of the world, therfore the world hateth you.

text: ye therefore beloued (seing you be warned afore hand) beware, leaste ye, with other men, be also plucked a waye through the errour of the wicked, and fall from your owne stedfastnesse.
verse_text: Ye therfore beloved seynge ye knowe it before hande beware lest ye be also plucked a waye with the erroure of the wicked and fall from youre awne stedfastnes:

verse_text: For euery man that euill doeth, hateth the light, neither commeth to light, least his deedes should be reprooued.

verse_text: And at that time will I searche Ierusalem with lightes, and visite the men that are frosen in their dregges, and say in their heartes, The Lord will neither doe good nor doe euill.

text: Iesus, dyd call together the twelue disciples, and gaue to them power ouer vncleane spirites that they should cast them out, and shoulde heale al maner of diseases, and infirmities.
verse_text: AND hauing called his twelue Disciples togeather, he gaue them power ouer vncleane Spirits, that they should cast them out, & should cure al manner of disease, & al manner of infirmitie.

text: Paul) the witnes of mine owne conscience, without remorse or grudge, for my conuersation hath be in simplicitie amonge you without carnall or crafty subteltie or deceipt, saith S.
verse_text: Neither yet did we euer vse flattering wordes, as ye knowe, nor coloured couetousnes, God is recorde.

text: And agayne he sayeth, As my father sente me, euen so I send you By these, and many such other places, we maye see, that our louyng *, did giue greate aucthoritie to his apostles.
verse_text: Because a more excellent spirit, and knowledge, and vnderstanding (for hee did expound dreames, and declare hard sentences, and dissolued doubtes) were founde in him, euen in Daniel, whome the King named Belteshazzar:

text: It followeth that the paschal lamb which Christ did eat with his disciples, was turned into the passeouer, because Christ said, the lab is the passouer, as it is written in luke;
verse_text: How he went into the house of God, and did take and eate the Shew bread, and gaue also to them that were with him, which it is not lawful to eate but for the Priests alone?

text: It is the spirit that ge ueth lyfe, the fleshe profiteth nothing, you shal vnderstande, that these wordes are taken of the catholyke church, in two most godly senses, the one is,
verse_text: For the pistles (sayth he) are sore and stronge: but his bodyly presence is weake and his speache rude.

text: And in luke he saith, iff any ma come to me ad hate not his father, his mother, his wife, his childern, his brethern and sisters, yea ad his own life, he can not be my disciple.
verse_text: If a man come to me and hate not his father and mother and wyfe and chyldren and brethren and sisters more over and his awne lyfe he cannot be my disciple.

text: & cum dies factus esset vocauit discipulos suos & elegit duodecim ex P A G Ecclxxxiii ipsis quos & apostolos nominauit Simonem, quem cognominauit Petrum & Andream fratrem eius.
verse_text: Tunc placuit Apostolis et senioribus cum omni ecclesia eligere viros ex eis, et mittere Antiochiam cum Paulo et Barnaba: Judam, qui cognominabatur Barsabas, et Silam, viros primos in fratribus:

text: Mathew and mark where he saith that all sinnes and blasphemies of men shall be forgeuen them, but he that shall blasphme against the holy gost, it shall neuer be forgeuen him.
verse_text: But he that shal blaspheme against the Holy Ghost, he hath not forgiuenesse for euer, but shal be guilty of an eternal sinne.

text: He hath appoynted a daye in the which he wil iudge the worlde by that man by who he hath appoynted, and hath offered faith vnto all men, after yt he had raysed hym from death.
verse_text: because he hath apoynted a daye in the which he will iudge the worlde acordynge to ryghtewesses by that man whom he hath apoynted and hath offered faith to all men after that he had raysed him from deeth.

text: But Abraham saied: sonne remember that thou in thy life tyme, receiuedest thy pleasure, and contrarywise Lazarus receiued pain, but now he is coforted, and thou art punished.
verse_text: And Abraham said to him: Sonne, remember that thou didst receiue good things in thy life time, and Lazarus likewise euil: but not he is comforted, and thou art tormented.

text: And that Saint Peter beinge at Rome, wrote this Epistle, and sent it from Rome, as well to such straungers as were dispersed and scattered abroade in the countreys of Pontus,
verse_text: For Paul had determined to saile by Ephesus, because hee woulde not spend the time in Asia: for he hasted to be, if hee could possible, at Hierusalem, at the day of Pentecost.

text: That Comforter, euen the holy ghoste, whom my father shall send in my name he shall teach you al thinges, and bring all to your remembraunce, what so euer I haue tolde you.
verse_text: But that comforter which is the holy gost (whom my father will sende in my name) he shall teache you all thinges and bringe all thinges to youre remembraunce whatsoever I have tolde you.

text: and that you may both mynd it, and folow it, for god is he, which worketh in you, bothe for to wyll it, and to performe it, after as it shall please him. to ye Philippi. 2.
verse_text: But not performe ye it also in deed: that as your mind is prompt to be willing, so it may be also to performe, of that which you haue.

text: And euen with one text in this gospel it is ouerthrowne where it is said, that Iacob begatte Ioseph the husband of Marie, of whom was borne Iesus, whiche is called Christ.
verse_text: And the Generation of Christ was in this wise. When his Mother MARIE was spoused to Ioseph, before they came together, she was found to be with a child, by the Holy Ghost.

text: but thou after thine hard heart that can not repente, doste hepe together the treasure of wrathe agaynst the day of vengeaunce and reuelation of the true iudgement of GOD.
verse_text: But thou after thyne harde herte that cannot repet heapest ye togedder the treasure of wrath agaynste the daye of vengeauce when shalbe opened the rightewes iudgement of god

text: And full of good fruites, that is to say, good workes, wheras of the other wisedomes cometh no goodnesse but it be colourable & vainglorious, or for some sinistre purpose,
verse_text: And if a man loue righteousnesse, her labours are vertues: for she teacheth temperance and prudence: iustice and fortitude, which are such things as men can haue nothing more profitable in their life.

text: Chap. A rod shall come forth oute of the stocke of Iesse oute of a stocke, whiche nowe is deade (sayth he) shall growe a braunche, that is oute of an olde withered stocke.
verse_text: But hee shall growe vp before him as a branche, and as a roote out of a dry grounde:

text: In this village there dwelled two women the name of the one was Martha, the others name was Mary, whiche women ioyfully receyued Christ and his disciples into their house.
verse_text: And in Ioppe there was a certaine Disciple named Tabitha, which by interpretation is called Dorcas. This woman was ful of good workes & almes-deeds which she did.

text: Fourthly by baptisme we die with Christ, and are buried (as it were) in his bloude & death, that we shoulde suffer afflictions and death, as Christ himself hath suffered.
verse_text: Are you ignorant that al we which are baptized in Christ IESVS, in his death we are baptized?

text: But Saule saueth the Fynge named Agag, and permitteth the people to saue the best and fattest of the bestiall, to the entent sacrifice shoulde be made thereof vnto God.
verse_text: And vnto the people that was found there, Iosias gaue thirtie thousand lambes, and kids, and three thousand calues: these things were giuen of the kings allowance, according as hee promised to the people, to the Priestes, and to the Leuites.

text: When thou art bidde to dinner to a mariage, thou shalt not set thy selfe in the highgest place, lest peraduenture one that is more honourable then thou, be also bidden.
verse_text: When thou art bidden of any man to a wedding, sit not downe in the highest roume: lest a more honourable man then thou be bidden of him,

text: Go, and teache all nations, and baptise them in the name of the father, the sonne, and the holy ghost. ^o^, here Christ doth attribute the godhead vnto the holy ghost:
verse_text: Go therfore and teache all nacions baptysinge them in the name of the father and the sonne and the holy goost:

text: A great prophet is risen amongst vs, and God hath visited his people. And contrary wise, where this worde is comprehended & in heart conceyued, there is Christ knowen,
verse_text: The Lord God looketh vpon vs, and in trueth hath comfort in vs, as Moises in his song, which witnessed to their faces declared, saying, And he shall be comforted in his seruants.

text: Et si iustus vix saluabitur, impius et peccator vbi parebunt And if a good ma shal scarsely and with much a do be saued, where shal the wicked & common sinner appeare?
verse_text: And if the iust man shal scarce be saued, where shal the impious & sinner appeare?

text: The kingdom of god is neither meate nor drinck, meaning to say that the kingdom of god, which is a spirituall thing, doth not stand in bodili things but in spiritual.
verse_text: For all things cannot be in men, because the son of man is not immortal, and they are delighted with the vanity of evil.

text: * I confesse, that I beleue christ * died for me, and I also with him and 1 page missing The tenth sermon domestical, vnto their chyldren, of the Ascention of Christ.
verse_text: THE Seniours therfore that are among you. I beseech, myself a fellow-Senior with them & a witnesse of the Passions of Christ, who am also partaker of that glorie which is to be reuealed in time to come:

text: The holy goost shall come vpon the, and the vertue of the highest shall ouershadow the, and therfore the thing that shalbe born holy, shalbe called the sonne of God.
verse_text: And the Angel answering, said to her: The Holy Ghost shal come vpon thee, and the power of the most High shal ouershadow thee. And therfore also that which of thee shal be borne Holy, shal be called the Sonne of God.

text: And after that he requireth loue towardes god (though he cannot giue it by the lawe) that we shuld loue god with all our hart, with all our soule with all our might.
verse_text: And that he be loued from the whole hart, and with the whole vnderstanding, and with the whole soule, and with the whole strength: and to loue his neighbour as himself, is a greater thing then al Holocausts and Sacrifices.

text: We do know (saith Paul) yt if our earthly mancio of thys dwelling wer destroyed, we haue a building of god, an habitacion not made wt handes, but eternall in heauen.
verse_text: FOR we know that if our earthly house of this habitation be dissolued, that we haue a building of God, a house not made with hand, eternal in Heauen.

text: Lorde, vnto who shal we go, thou hast the woordes of eternal life, and wee do beleue and we haue knowen, that thou art the same Christ, the sonne of the liuyng God?
verse_text: But we know that that Sone of God is come, and hath giue vs a mind to know him, which is true: and we are in him that is true, that is, in that his Sone Iesus Christ: this same is that very God, and that eternal life.

text: For by and by after the circumcision of his sonne Iohn, he was fylled with the holy ghost, and prophecyed, praisyng god, that had giuen that greate grace vnto him.
verse_text: Because a more excellent spirit, and knowledge, and vnderstanding (for hee did expound dreames, and declare hard sentences, and dissolued doubtes) were founde in him, euen in Daniel, whome the King named Belteshazzar:

text: so God the Father loued the world, that he woulde geue his dearling, his owne only sonne, that all that beleue in hym should not perish, but haue euerlasting lyfe.
verse_text: For God so loued þ world, that he gaue his only begotten Sonne: that whosoeuer beleeueth in him, should not perish, but haue euerlasting life.

text: Paule saith) can not purge the coscience of them that serueth in them, for it is not possible sinne to be taken away by the bloude of bullockes or goates. Hebr. x.
verse_text: Which was a similitude for the tyme then present and in which were offered gyftes and sacrifises that coulde not make them that minister parfecte as pertaynynge to the conscience

text: it shalbe declared vnto you, bothe howe it is lawfull for christian people to sweare, and also what perill and daunger it is, vainly to sweare, or to be forsworne.
verse_text: And of other things beside these, my sone, take thou heede: for there is none ende in making many bookes, and much reading is a wearines of the flesh.

text: Et dimitte nobis debita nostra sicut et nos dimittimus debitoribus nostris, that is to say Forgyue vs our trespssaes as we forgyue them that trespasse agaynst vs.
verse_text: Et dimitte nobis peccata nostra, siquidem et ipsi dimittimus omni debenti nobis. Et ne nos inducas in tentationem.

text: Finally, we altogether (whether we be men or women) must confesse, that we be regenerate into a liuinge hope, through the resurrection of Christ Iesu, from death.
verse_text: For, for this cause also was it euangelized to the dead: that they may be iudged indeed according to men, in the flesh: but may liue according to God in the Spirit.

text: What man of you hauing an hundreth sheep, if he lose one of the, doth not leaue nynty & nine in the wildernes, and goeth after ye which is lost vntill he fynd it?
verse_text: What man of you hauing an hundred sheep: and if he hath lost one of them, doth he not leaue the ninetie nine in the desert, and goeth after that which was lost vntil he find it?

text: That their is more ioye in heauen vpon one sinner that hathe repentaunce, then vpon foure score and ninetye iuste, that thinke they haue no neede of repentaunce.
verse_text: I say vnto you, that likewise ioy shall be in heauen for one sinner that conuerteth, more then for ninetie and nine iust men, which neede none amendment of life.

text: Behold the lambe of god, that taketh away the sinnes of the world, his works and miracles wer testimonies yt his doctrine was of god, wel, al this wil not serue.
verse_text: He saued other; himself he can not saue: if he be the King of Israel, let him now come downe from the Crosse, and we wil beleeue him.

text: As Ionas was in the belly os the whale, three dayes and three nyghtes, so shall the sonne of man be in the harte of the grounde, three dayes, and three nyghtes.
verse_text: For as Ionas was thre dayes and thre nyghtes in the whales belly: soo shall the sonne of man be thre dayes and thre nyghtes in the hert of the erth.

text: Those that are beside the waye, are they that heare, then cometh the deuell, and taketh away the word out of theyr hartes, lest they shuld beleue and bee saued.
verse_text: And they besides the way, are those that heare, then the Diuel commeth, and taketh the Word out of their hart, lest beleeuing they be saued.

text: Si remiseritis hominibus erra ta sua remittet & vobis pater vester celestis Quod si non remiseritis hominibus errata sua nec pater remittet vobis errata vestra.
verse_text: Quod si vos non dimiseritis: nec Pater vester, qui in caelis est, dimittet vobis peccata vestra.

text: Behold, here Paul hath placed it underneth one fruit and commoditie, because we should bee one breade and one bodye, for all wee be partakers of the same bread:
verse_text: because that we (though we be many) yet are one breed and one bodye in as moch as we all are partetakers of one breed.

text: & had finished that excellent sermon made then vnto his disciples, he went furth with his disciples ouer ye broke called Cedro, into a certain garden, to pray.
verse_text: WHEN IESVS had said these things, he went forth with his Disciples beyond the Torrent-Cedron, where was a garden, into the which he entred and his Disciples.

text: Agayne, the deuell taketh hym vp, into an exceding high mountaine, and sheweth hym all the kingdomes of the worlde, and the glory of them, and sayeth vnto hym:
verse_text: Againe the Deuill taketh him vp into an exceeding high mountaine, and sheweth him all the kingdomes of the world, and the glory of them:

text: father Abraham haue mercie on me, and send Lazarus that he maie dippe the tippe of his finger in water, and coole my tongue, for I am tormented in this flambe.
verse_text: Father Abraham, haue mercie on me, and send Lazarus that he may dip the tip of his finger into water for to coole my tongue, because I am tormented in this flame.

text: When the Apostle sayeth to those that be maried, that the time which remaineth is but short and that they whyche haue wyues, should be althoughe they had none.
verse_text: For there are some eunuches, which were so borne of their mothers belly: and there be some eunuches, which be gelded by men: and there be some eunuches, which haue gelded them selues for the kingdome of heauen. He that is able to receiue this, let him receiue it.

text: You were once like shepe strayed oute of Gods flocke, but nowe you be conuerted and turned againe to the pastor and feder, bishop and ouerseer of your soules.
verse_text: For ye were as shepe goinge astraye: but are now returned vnto the shepheerd and bisshoppe of youre soules.

text: that the bodyes shoulde not remaine on the crosse on the Sabboth daye (for the Sabboth day was an hyghe day) besought Pylate that their legges might ve broken
verse_text: The Iewes therfore (because it was the Parasceue) that the bodies might not remaine vpon the crosse on the Sabboth (for that was a great Sabboth day) they desired Pilate that their legges might be broken, and they might be taken away.

text: All we yt are baptised, are buried wt Christe in to death, that as Christ rose agayne, by the glorie of his father, so we also should walke in newnes of lyfe.
verse_text: We are buryed with him by baptism for to dye that lykewyse as Christ was raysed vp from deeth by the glorye of the father: even so we also shuld walke in a newe lyfe.

text: Caste me not awaie from thy face, and take not away thy holy spirit fro me. Lorde turne not away thy face from me, cast not thy seruaunt away in displeasure.
verse_text: Hide not therefore thy face from mee, nor cast thy seruat away in displeasure: thou hast bene my succour: leaue me not, neither forsake mee, O God of my saluation.

text: And so of the contrary part, that which is by workes is not by grace, els grace shuld not be grace, nor workes (that is to say desertes) shuld not be workes.
verse_text: Yf it be of grace the is it not of workes. For then were grace no moare grace. Yf it be of workes then is it no moare grace. For then were deservyng no lenger deservynge.

text: For it was neuer sayd to any of them, whatsoeuer thou loosest on earth, shal be losed in heauen, whatsoeuer thou bindest on earth, shall be bounde in heauen.
verse_text: And I will giue vnto thee the keyes of the kingdome of heauen: and whatsoeuer thou shalt bind on earth, shall be bound in heauen: whatsoeuer thou shalt loose on earth, shall be loosed in heauen.

text: And to the Colosseis it is said, that it hath pleased the father to recocile all things to him bi Christ, being pacified by the blood of christes own crosse.
verse_text: But al of God, who hath reconciled vs to himself by Christ: and hath giuen vs the ministerie of reconciliation.

text: Loe, accursed (saith he) is al no acception, al sayth God which continueth not, in al thinges (for he that is giltie of one is giltie of the whole layeth S.
verse_text: But whoso loketh in the parfaict lawe of libertie and continueth ther in (yf he be not a forgetfull hearer but a doar of the worke) the same shall be happie in his dede.

text: Let ye vngodly (sayth he) forsake his euil way, and the vnrightwise man his ymaginacions, and let him returne vnto the Lord, and he wyll haue mercy vpo him:
verse_text: Let the wicked forsake his way, and the unjust man his thoughts, and let him return to the Lord, and he will have mercy on him, and to our God:

text: The hired seruaunt flieth, bicause he is an hyred seruaunt and careth not for the sheepe I am the good sheeph^rd and knowe my sheepe, and am knowen of myne.
verse_text: I am the good shepheard, and know my sheepe, and am knowen of mine.

text: & they which haue done good, shall come fourth vnto the resurrectio of lyfe, but they which haue done euil, shall come fourth vnto resurrectio of iudgemet.
verse_text: and they that haue done good things, shal come forth into the resurrection of life: but they that haue done euil into the resurrection of iudgement.

text: Cursed be he, that shall make a grauen or molten ymage, abhominable before ye Lorde, the worke of an artificers hande, and shall set it in a secrete place.
verse_text: Cursed be the man that maketh any grauen or molten image, an abomination vnto the Lord, the worke of the handes of the craftesman, and putteth it in a secret place:

text: I am the bread of lyfe And a litle after, he saith, if you shall not eat the flesh of the sonne of man and drink his blood, you shall not haue lyfe in you.
verse_text: Amen, amen I say to you, Vnles you eate the flesh of the Sonne of man, and drinke his bloud, you shal not haue life in you.

text: Christ did beare in his body our synnes, vpon the crosse, where by we beinge dead to sinne, should lyue vnto iustice, with whose strypes wee are made hole,
verse_text: Who himself bare our sinnes in his body vpon the tree: that dead to sinnes, we may liue to iustice. By whose stripes you are healed.

text: Paule. What so euer things are written afore tyme, are written for oure learninge, that we thorough pacience and comfort of the scripture, might haue hope.
verse_text: Whatsoever thinges are written afore tyme are written for oure learnynge that we thorow pacience and comforte of the scripture myght have hope.

text: No. Therefore let vs (as Christ comandeth vs) seke first the kingdom of god, and the righteousnes thereof, and all these thinges shal be ministred vnto vs.
verse_text: Seeke therefore first the Kingdom of God, and the iustice of him, and al these things shal be giuen you besides.

text: I pray you for the mercye of God, that you giue your bodies as an holye hoste, as a liuing sacrifice pleasant to almighty God by our sauiour Iesus Christ.
verse_text: Let vs therefore by him offer the sacrifice of prayse alwaies to God, that is, the fruite of the lippes, which confesse his Name.

text: Mountaines shalbe moued, and hylles shal tremble, but my mercy shal not depart from the, and my leage of peace shall not be moued sayth the merciful Lord.
verse_text: Moyses said: When I shal be gone forth out of the citie, I wil stretch forth my handes to our Lord, and the thunders shal cease, and the haile shal not be: that thou maist know that the earth is our Lords:

text: Blessed is the man, that goeth not in the councell of the vngodly, that abideth not in the way of synners, and setteth not in the seate of the scornefull.
verse_text: Blessed is the man that doeth not walke in the counsell of the wicked, nor stand in the way of sinners, nor sit in ye seate of the scornefull:

text: by him (that is by Christ) we allwaies offer vp the sacrifice of thanks geuing vnto god (that is to say) the frute of oure lippes that confesse his name.
verse_text: For by him offer we the sacrifice of laude allwayes to god: that is to saye the frute of those lyppes which confesse his name.

text: And ye when ye were dead through sinne, and through the vncircumcision of your flesh, hath he quickened with him, and hath forgiuen vs all our trespaces.
verse_text: And you being dead in your sinnes, and the vncircumcision of your flesh, hath hee quickened together with him, hauing forgiuen you all trespasses,

text: Eratis illo in tempore sine christo, alienatia conuersatione Israel, et hospites testamentorum, promissionis spem non habentes, et sine deo in hoc mundo.
verse_text: Juxta fidem defuncti sunt omnes isti, non acceptis repromissionibus, sed a longe eas aspicientes, et salutantes, et confitentes quia peregrini et hospites sunt super terram.

text: Commeth down from heauen, that is from hys own pryde, and false excellency, for (as Christ sayeth) no man goeth vp into heauen but he that commeth down,
verse_text: But the iustice which is of faith, saith thus: Say not in thy hart, Who shal ascend into Heauen? that is to bring Christ downe.

text: Non ergo quocumque modo quisqua manducauerit carnem Christi, et biberit sanguinem Christi, manet in Christo, et in illo Christus, sed certo quodam modo:
verse_text: Itaque quicumque manducaverit panem hunc, vel biberit calicem Domini indigne, reus erit corporis et sanguinis Domini.

text: Eade hora. Is not this Babilo the great city that I haue builded for a palaice of mi kingdom in the might of my manlines, and in the glory of my beauty.
verse_text: And Dauid said, Solomon my sonne is yong and tender, and the house that is to be builded for the Lord, must be exceeding magnificall, of fame and of glory throughout all countreys:

text: Iesus walked (sayth the Euangelist) by the sea of Galile, he sawe Simon Peter, and Adrewe his brother castyng a nette into the sea, and sayd vnto them:
verse_text: As he walked by the see of Galile he sawe Simon and Andrew his brother castinge nettes into the see for they were fysshers.

text: He was not weake in faith, neither cosidered his own body, dead in maner, (for he was now almost an hundreth yeare old) nor the baraine wombe of Sarah.
verse_text: And being not weake in faith, hee considered not his owne body now dead, when hee was about an hundred yere old, neither yet the deadnes of Saraes wombe.

text: And she had bene a widowe aboue foure score & foure yere, which departed not from the temple, but serueth God with fastinges and prayers nyght and day.
verse_text: And she was a widow of about fourescore and foure yeeres, which departed not from the Temple, but serued God with fastings and prayers night and day.

text: witchcraft, enuie, strife, contencion, wrathe, sedicion, murthers, dronkenes, glottonie, blasphemy slouthfulnes, ydlenes, baudy talking, sclaunderinge.
verse_text: thefts, auarices, wickednesse, guile, impudicities, an euil eye, blasphemie, pride, foolishnes.

text: & who so euer knoweth not the scriptures, knoweth not ye power & vertue of God, it foloweth that he that knoweth not ye scriptures, knoweth not Christ,
verse_text: Therfore he that despiseth these things, despiseth not man but God, who also hath giuen his holy Spirit in vs.

text: And if we receyue the witnesse of menne, why shuld we not take the witnesse of god (which is infinitely greater than mas) that he is the sonne of god?
verse_text: Do ye not know that the sainctes shall iudge the worlde? If the worlde shalbe iudged by you: are ye not good ynough to iudge smale trifles:

text: And this: ye can not dryncke of the cuppe of God, and of the cup of the deuilles, ye can not be partakers of Gods table, and of the table of deuilles.
verse_text: Ye cannot drincke of the cup of the lorde and of that cup of the deuyls. Ye cannot be partetakers of the lordes table and of the table of deuelles.

text: Cum facis prandium aut coenam, noli vocare amicos tuos, neque fratres, neque cognatos, neque vicinos diuites, nequando & ipsi te vicissim inuitentac.
verse_text: Si autem manus tua, vel pes tuus scandalizat te, abscide eum, et projice abs te: bonum tibi est ad vitam ingredi debilem, vel claudum, quam duas manus vel duos pedes habentem mitti in ignem aeternum.

text: Colimus ergo et imperatorem sic, quomodo et nobis licet, et ipsi expedit, ut hominem deo secundum, et quicquid est, deo consecutum, solo deo minorem,
verse_text: Quicumque sunt sub jugo servi, dominos suos omni honore dignos arbitrentur, ne nomen Domini et doctrina blasphemetur.

text: that I shall sende an hunger into the earthe, not the hunger of breade, neither the thruste of water, but an hunger to heare the worde of the lorde.
verse_text: For I will multiplie the fruite of the trees, and the increase of the fielde, that ye shall beare no more the reproch of famine among the heathen.

text: Seniores ergo qui in vobis sunt obsecro, consenior & testis Christi passionum, qui & eius quae in futuro reuelanda est glorie communicator, pascite.
verse_text: Qui nunc gaudeo in passionibus pro vobis, et adimpleo ea quae desunt passionem Christi, in carne mea pro corpore ejus, quod est Ecclesia:

text: Therfore sayd Paul, trie your selues, make some profe of your selues, is it possible that ye should not knowe Christ in you, if ye be not reprobate?
verse_text: Wherfore, Brethren, labour the more that by good workes you may make sure your vocation and election. For doing these things, you shal not sinne at any time.

text: Furthermore, to be iustified, as ye haue heard ofte, is to obtayne the forgeuenes of sinnes, or els of an vniust man to be made iust. Ephe.ij. chap.
verse_text: And if a man desire multitude of knowledge: she knoweth thinges past, & coniectureth of thinges to come: she knoweth the subtilities of wordes, and the solution of arguments: she knoweth signes and wonders before they be done, and the euentes of times and ages.

text: Moses brake the two tables, whiche he had receiued at Gods hand, when he sawe the Israelites daunsyng aboute a calfe, and caused to be killed.xxiii.
verse_text: AND the people seeing that Moyses made tariance ere he came downe from the mount, being assembled against Aaron, they sayd: Arise, make vs goddes, that may goe before vs: for what hath chanced to this Moyses the man that brought vs out of the Land of AEgypt, we know not.

text: Dathan and Abyron, which for their obstinate and greedie desyre sanke into Hell, the earth opened and swalowed them vp, with all theyr confederacie.
verse_text: Strangers conspired together against him, and maligned him in the wildernesse, euen the men that were of Dathans, and Abirons side, and the congregation of Core with fury and wrath.

text: I haue desired and wished to be seperate & deuided from Christe for the loue that I haue to my brethren, that be my carnall kinsmen the Israelites.
verse_text: And I wil very gladly spend and bee spent for you, though the more abundantly I loue you, the lesse I bee loued.

text: So lykewise shal my heauenly father do also vnto you, if ye from your heartes forgiue not euerye one his brother their trespasses. THE EXPOSITION.
verse_text: So likewise shall mine heauenly Father doe vnto you, except ye forgiue from your hearts, eche one to his brother their trespasses.

text: Euery man at the beginning doth set forth good wine and whe me be dronken, then that which is worse, but thou hast kept the good wine vntill nowe.
verse_text: and saith to him: Euery man first setteth the good wine, and when they haue wel drunke, then that which is worse. But thou hast kept the good wine vntil now.

text: Prouer. xvi. Melior est patiens viro forti & qui dominatur animo suo expugnatore vrbiu Better is the pacient man, then he that is strong of bodye:
verse_text: Melior est homo qui minuitur sapientia, et deficiens sensu, in timore, quam qui abundat sensu, et transgreditur legem Altissimi.

text: He that heareth my word, and beleue in him that sent me, hath euerlastinge life, and shall not come into iudgemente, but passe from death to life.
verse_text: Amen, amen I say to you, that he which heareth my word, and beleeueth him that sent me, hath life euerlasting: and he commeth not into iudgement, but shal passe from death into life.

text: F Or God so loued the world, that he gaue his only begotten sonne, that whosoeuer beleueth in him, shoulde not perishe, but haue euerlasting life.
verse_text: For God so loued þ world, that he gaue his only begotten Sonne: that whosoeuer beleeueth in him, should not perish, but haue euerlasting life.

text: Blessed art thou Simon, the sonne of Ioanna, for fleshe and bloude hath not this reueiled, and opened vnto the, but my father whiche is in heauen.
verse_text: happy arte thou Simon the sonne of Ionas for fleshe and bloud hath not opened vnto the that but my father which is in heven.

text: so that Dauid and one Abisai with him, came in the night into Saules hoste, wher Saule lay slepyng, and his speare stacke in the groud at his hed.
verse_text: So Dauid and Abishai came to the people by night, and behold, Saul lay sleeping within the trench, and his speare stucke in the ground at his bolster:

text: & offert se ipse quasi Sacerdos ut peccata nostra dimittat, hic in imagine, ibi in ueritate, ubi apud patrem pro nobis quasi aduocatus interuenit.
verse_text: Quia et Christus semel pro peccatis nostris mortuus est, justus pro injustis, ut nos offerret Deo, mortificatus quidem carne, vivificatus autem spiritu.

text: Ita et quae dei sunt nemo nouit nisi spiritus dei, what man knoweth the thinges whiche are in man, but the spirite of manne whiche is within him?
verse_text: For what man knoweth the things of a man, saue the spirite of a man, which is in him?

text: Hee shall bee ledde as a sheepe vnto the slaughter, and as a lambe before the sherer, so shal he hold his peace, and he shall not open his mouth?
verse_text: hee is brought as a sheepe to the slaughter, and as a sheepe before her shearer is dumme, so he openeth not his mouth.

text: Timor non est in charitate sed perfecta charitas foras mittit timorem, quoniam timor penam habe^, qui autem timet non est perfectus in charitate.
verse_text: nam qui sine timore est non poterit justificari: iracundia enim animositatis illius subversio illius est.

text: And Dauid said furthermore: as sure as the lord liueth, the lord shal smite him, or his day shall come to dye, or he shall descend into battaill,
verse_text: Dauid said furthermore, As the Lord liueth, the Lord shal smite him, or his day shall come to die, or hee shall descend into battell, and perish.

text: for there is no power but of god, the powers that are, ar ordeyned of god. who so euer therfore resisteth power, resisteth the ordinance of god:
verse_text: Let euery soul be subiect to higher powers, for there is no power but of God. And those that are, of God are ordeined.

text: Sicut enim fuit Ionas in * ceti tribus *, et tris bus noctibus, sic erit filius hominis in corde terre, tribus diebus & tribus * That is to say:
verse_text: et erat Jonas in ventre piscis tribus diebus et tribus noctibus.

text: Euery thing that is cosecrated to the lord, saith god, whether it be ma, beast, or felde, shall not be sold nor can not be redemed or raunsomed.
verse_text: Notwithstanding, nothing separate from the common vse that a man doeth separate vnto the Lord of all that he hath (whether it bee man or beast, or lande of his inheritance) may be solde nor redeemed:

text: If we (saith he) or an Angel from heauen, shoulde preache vnto you an other gospel, besides, or cotrary to that ye haue receiued, curssed be he.
verse_text: But although we, or an Angel from Heauen, euangelize to you beside that which we haue euangelized to you, be he anathema.

text: If they (saith he) heare not Moses and the Prophetes, (that is holye scriptures, neither will, theye beleue thoughe one rose from deathe againe.
verse_text: If they heare not Moses and the prophetes nether will they beleve though one roose from deeth agayne.

text: Mat. v. Diligite inimicos vestros benefacite hijs qui oderunt vos ^t orate pro persequentibus et caluniantibus vos vt sitis filij patris vestri.
verse_text: Verumtamen diligite inimicos vestros: benefacite, et mutuum date, nihil inde sperantes: et erit merces vestra multa, et eritis filii Altissimi, quia ipse benignus est super ingratos et malos.

text: I will take downe and breake mine old barnes, and I will make them larger, and there I wyll bestowe and laye vp myne encrease and all my goodes:
verse_text: I will destroye my barnes and bilde greater and therin will I gadder all my frutes and my goodes:

text: but they shalbe punished with perpetuall and inextinquible fire. and as Esay saith, where their worme doth not dye and the fyer goeth neuer out.
verse_text: the Lord almighty will take vengeance of them in the day of iudgement in putting fire & wormes in their flesh, and they shall feele them and weepe for euer.

text: euen the fathers, that euery man that seeth the sone and beleueth in him, should haue life eternal, and I wyl againe rayse him in the last day.
verse_text: that euery one that seeth the Sonne, and beleeueth in him, haue life euerlasting, & I wil raise him in the last day.

text: Thou shalte not kill, thou shalt not commit adultery, thou shalt not steale, thou shalte not beare false witnesse, honor thy father and mother,
verse_text: Thou knowest the comandements, Thou shalt not commit adulterie. Thou shalt not kill. Thou shalt not steale. Thou shalt not beare false witnesse. Thou shalt hurt no man. Honour thy father and mother.

text: Christ saith: Excepte youre righteousnes exceede the righteousnes of the scribes and Phariseis, ye canne not entre into the kingdome of heauen.
verse_text: For I saye vnto you except youre rightewesnes excede the righetewesnes of the Scribes and Pharises ye cannot entre into the kyngdome of heven.

text: Now sayd they, we beleue that Christ is the sauior of the worlde, not because thou hast said so, but because we know it our selues to be true.
verse_text: But this I confesse to thee, that according to the sect, which they cal heresie, I doe so serue the Father my God, beleeuing al things that are written in the Law & the Prophets:

text: There is one fayth, whiche in scripture is called a dead faythe, whiche bryngeth furth no good workes, but is idle, barrain, and vnfruitefull.
verse_text: For the letters, sayeth hee, are sore and strong, but his bodily presence is weake, and his speache is of no value.

text: So saith also christ Iohn the xi. of Lazarus, our fred Lazarus sleapeth, but I go that I may raise him vp from sleape, than his diciples said,
verse_text: This sayde he and after that he sayde vnto the: oure frende Lazarus slepeth but I goo to wake him out of slepe.

text: As it is written, bring vnto me no more youre vayne sacrifices, your burnt offeringes is abomination, your new moones, sabboths & conuentios,
verse_text: Saying before, Because hosts and oblations & holocausts, & for sinne thou wouldest not, neither did they please thee, which are offered according to the law,

text: that disciple was knowen vnto the high priest, and went in with Iesus into the palace of the high priest But Peter stode at the dore without.
verse_text: that disciple was knowen vnto the high Priest, and went in with Iesus into the palace of the high Priest.

text: For as a braunche cannot beare fruit of it self (saith our sauior Christ) except it abide in the vine, so cannot you, except you abide in me:
verse_text: Abide in me: and I in you. As the branch can not beare fruit of it self, vnles it abide in the vine, so you neither vnles you abide in me.

text: For it is written in the thirde of Matthewe, that euery tree, that bringeth not forth good fruite, shalbe cut downe, and caste into the fyre.
verse_text: therefore euery tree which bringeth not foorth good fruite, shalbe hewen downe, and cast into the fire.

text: he that beleueth on me, the workes that I do, the same shall he do also, and greater workes then these shal he do, because I go to my father:
verse_text: he that beleveth on me the workes that I doo the same shall he do and greater workes then these shall he do because I go vnto my father.

text: Gala. v. Vos in libertatem vocati estis fratres, tantum ne libertatem in occasionem detis carnis sed per charitatem spiritus seruite inuicem.
verse_text: Nolite fraudare invicem, nisi forte ex consensu ad tempus, ut vacetis orationi: et iterum revertimini in idipsum, ne tentet vos Satanas propter incontinentiam vestram.

text: God so loued the worlde, that he gaue hys only begotten sonne, that whosoeuer beleueth in hym, shulde not perysh, but haue euerlastynge lyfe.
verse_text: For God so loveth the worlde that he hath geven his only sonne that none that beleve in him shuld perisshe: but shuld have everlastinge lyfe.

text: For thus sayth Christ: He that entreth not in at the doore into the shepefolde, but clymeth vppe another way, he is a thefe and a murtherer.
verse_text: AMEN, amen I say to you, he that entreth not by the doore into the fold of the sheep, but climeth vp another way; he is a theefe and a robber.

text: And agayne he sayeth. He that loueth me, will kepe my woorde, and my father wyll loue hym, and we wyll bothe come to him, and dwel with him.
verse_text: IESVS answered, and said to him: If any loue me, he wil keepe my worde, and my Father wil loue him, and we wil come to him, and wil make abode with him.

text: Quorum fidem vt vidit, dixit, homo remittuntur tibi peccata tua, et ait paralitico tibi dico, surge, tolle lectum tuum & vade in domum tuam.
verse_text: Ut autem sciatis quia Filius hominis habet potestatem in terra dimittendi peccata, (ait paralytico) tibi dico, surge, tolle lectum tuum, et vade in domum tuam.

text: And Paul to the hebrews, per ipsum offerimus hostiam laudis semper deo that is thorow him we offer the sacrifice of praise alwais vnto god.
verse_text: For by him offer we the sacrifice of laude allwayes to god:

text: no solum in carne, sed & in spiritu, quia vana est castitas carnis, vbi regnat incontinentia spiritus, et caetera quae coinquin anta nimam,
verse_text: Sed cura est illi non quia laboraturus est, nec quoniam brevis illi vita est: sed concertatur aurificibus et argentariis; sed et aerarios imitatur, et gloriam praefert, quoniam res supervacuas fingit.

text: Si hodie obedieris populo huic & seruieris & peticioni eorum censeris locutusque fueris ad eos verba leuia erant tibi serui cunctis diebus.

text: Gala. iii. Christus nos redemit de maledictione legis factus pro nobis maledictum, quia scriptum est, maledictus Omnis qui pendet in ligno.

text: Ve uobis scribe et phariseihypocritae, quiae clauditis regnum celorum ante homines. uos enim non intratis, nec introeuntes sinitis intrare,

text: I pray yow that yow will giue vp or offer your bodies an holy, liuing, ad pleasing host vnto god, which is your reasonable seruing of god.
verse_text: I BESEECH you therfore, Brethren, by the mercie of God, that you exhibit your bodies a liuing Host holy, pleasing God, your reasonable seruice.

text: That is brought to passe, when I heare the gospel preached, in the which remission of sinnes is geuen to all mortall creatures, by Christ.

text: Iusticia iusti non liberabit eu in quacuque die peccauerit & impietas impij no nocebit ei in quacuque die couersus fuerit ab ipietate sua.

verse_text: So likewise you, except ye vtter by the tongue words easie to be vnderstood, how shall it be knowen what is spoken?

text: Therfore the bloude of Christ once offered remayneth for euer, for purgation of all synnes, and so resteth then no sacrifice in the masse.
verse_text: which hath not necessitie daily (as the Priestes) first for his owne sinnes to offer Hostes, then for the peoples. For this he did once, in offering himself.

text: For God knowethe that whatsoeuer daye you shall eate thereof, youre eyes shalbe opened, and you shalbe like Gods, knowynge good and euyll.
verse_text: For God doeth know, that in the day ye eate thereof, then your eyes shalbee opened: and yee shall bee as Gods, knowing good and euill.

verse_text: For ye haue not receiued the Spirit of bodage, to feare againe: but ye haue receiued the Spirit of adoption, whereby we cry Abba, Father.

text: The foules of the ayer (saith he) doth neither sowe nor reape, nor yet carry into the barnes, and yet your heauenly father feedeth them.
verse_text: Behold the foules of the ayre, that they sow not, neither reape, nor gather into barnes: and your heauenly father feedeth them.

text: In uno spiritu omnes nos in * pus baptizati sumus, siue dei, siue gentiles, siue serui, siue liberi & omnes in uno spiritu potati sumus.

text: And, No man knoweth the sonne but the father, neither knoweth any man the father but the sonne, and he to whom the sonne will open him.
verse_text: neither knoweth any man ye Father, but the Sonne, and he to whom ye Sonne will reueile him.

text: In quibus sunt quedam difficilia intellectu que indocti et instabiles deprauat sicut et ceteras scripturas ad suam ipsorum perditionem.

text: Whosoeuer denyeth me before men, him will I also denye before my father whiche is in heauen. The other folowyng of Christ is spiritual,

text: For he that eateth and drynketh vnworthely, eateth and drynketh hys owne damnation, because he maketh no difference of the lordes body.
verse_text: For he that eateth or drinketh vnworthely eateth and drynketh his awne damnacion because he maketh no difference of the lordis body.

text: For he tooke breade, and after he had geuen thankes he distributed them to his disciples, and the disciples to the that were set downe.
verse_text: And taking the Seauen loaues & the fishes, and giuing thankes, he brake, & gaue it to his Disciples, and the Disciples gaue to the People.

text: The text saith thus. Et facta collatione duo decim milia dragmas argenti, misit Ierosolima offerri pro peccatis mortuorum, sacrificium.
verse_text: Cumque efferrent pecuniam quae illata fuerat in templum Domini, reperit Helcias sacerdos librum legis Domini per manum Moysi.

text: Take me and cast me into the sea, so shal it let you be in rest, for I wote it is for my sake that this great tempest is come vpon you.
verse_text: Be not affraid, neither let it seeme to you a hard case that you did sel me into these countries: for God sent me before you into AEgypt for your preseruation.

text: The body is sowen in corruption, reproche, feblenesse & is a beastly body, but it riseth again without corruption, in glory, in power,
verse_text: It is sowen in dishonour, it shal rise in glorie. It is sowen in infirmitie, it shal rise in power.

text: Scripture sayth, Hoc aute a semetipso no. dixit, sed cu, esset pontifex anni illius, prophetauit, quod Iesus moriturus erat pro gente.
verse_text: Pater noster mortuus est in deserto, nec fuit in seditione, quae concitata est contra Dominum sub Core, sed in peccato suo mortuus est: hic non habuit mares filios. Cur tollitur nomen illius de familia sua, quia non habuit filium? date nobis possessionem inter cognatos patris nostri.

text: And whatsouer ye aske in my name that wyll I do, that the father may be glorifyed by the sonne, if ye shall aske any thyng in my name,
verse_text: And whatsoeuer ye aske in my Name, that will I doe, that the Father may be glorified in the Sonne.

text: thou foole, this night thei shal fetche awaie thy soule again fro thee, then whose shall those thynges bee, whiche thou hast prouided?
verse_text: But God sayde vnto him: Thou fole this night will they fetche awaye thy soule agayne from the. Then whose shall thoose thinges be which thou hast provyded?

text: Caro concupiscit aduersus spiritum, spiritus autem aduersus carnem, so that he called afore the mynde, here he calleth it the spirite.
verse_text: Because that the flesshly mynde is emnyte agaynst God: for it is not obedient to the lawe of God nether can be.

text: And S. Paul saith: If there be any man that shall not prouide for his, and especiall for his housholde, he is worse then an Infidele.
verse_text: But if any man haue not care of his owne and especially of his domesticals, he hath denied the faith, and is worse then an infidel.

text: Also whan Christ sayd, A ccipite spiritum sanctum, quorum remiseritis peccata, remittuntur eis, et quorum retinueritis, retenta sunt,
verse_text: Si enim dimiseritis hominibus peccata eorum: dimittet et vobis Pater vester caelestis delicta vestra.

text: A contrite and a troubled hart for a mannes sinnes the Prophet in the psalme calleth a sacrifice which almighty God will not despise.
verse_text: And to depart from injustice, is to offer a propitiatory sacrifice for injustices, and a begging of pardon for sins.

text: Thy siluer is drosse, it is not fine, it is counterfaite, thy siluer is turned, thou haddest good syluer What pertayned that to Esay?
verse_text: The gold also which they haue, is for bewtie, vnles a man wype of the rust, they shal not shine: for neither when they were moulten, did they feele.

text: &c. I know not to what purpose they should say it, hauing no harp nor other musicall instrument, which Dauid vsid to praise god with.
verse_text: He set singers also before the Altar, that by their voyces they might make sweet melody, and daily sing praises in their songs.

text: For he yt hath much riches is not damned, but he whose hart is set vppon riches. For as Paule saith, we shulde be as hauing nothing,
verse_text: But his care is, not because he shal labour, nor because he hath a short life, but he contendeth with goldsmithes and siluer smithes:

text: Tel them also, that Christ himselfe wil go before them into Galilee, wher they shall see him. and haue these things declared of him:
verse_text: And going quickly tel ye his Disciples that he is risen: and behold he goeth before you into Galilee: there you shal see him. Loe I haue foretold you.

text: Debuit per omnia fratribus assimulari, vt misericors fieret, et fidelis pontifex, ad deum, vt repropitiaret delicta populi, that is,
verse_text: Omnis namque pontifex ex hominibus assumptus, pro hominibus constituitur in iis quae sunt ad Deum, ut offerat dona, et sacrificia pro peccatis:

text: It is a thing most certen, that he that looseth Christ, loseth euery thing, and he that possesseth him, possesseth euery good thing.
verse_text: When it is present, men take example at it, and when it is gone they desire it: it weareth a crown, and triumpheth for euer, hauing gotten the victorie, striuing for vndefiled rewards.

text: And sometyme it is not profitable to aunswer a foole, accordyng to his foolishnesse, least the wise manne bee made like to ye foole.
verse_text: Be thou consentynge to thin aduersarie soone, while thou art in the weie with hym, lest perauenture thin aduersarie take thee to the domesman, and the domesman take thee to the mynystre, and thou be sent in to prisoun.

text: Thou shalte loue God aboue all thinges, with thy whole hearte, with thy whole soule, with all thy strength, and with all thy mynde:

text: But when the king hard therof, he was wroth and sent forth his me of warre and destroied those murtherers, and bret vp their citie.

text: dyd you neuer reade: The stone whiche the builders reproued and caste by, was made the heade stone for the corner of the buyldinge?

text: Roma. v. Si vnius delicto multi mortui sunt, multo magis gratia dei & donum vnius hominis Iesu Christi in plures homines abundauit.

text: Euery Scribe taught vnto the kyngdome of heauen, is like an housholder, which bringeth furth of his treasure thynges newe and olde,

text: And againe, the kyngdome of heauen is likened vnto a lytle nette that is cast into the sea, whiche did pull vp all kynde of fyshes.

text: For he that loueth hys father or mother, sonne, or doughter, house or lad, more then me (saieth Christ) is not worthy to haue me.

verse_text: Euery branch in me, not bearing fruit, he wil take it away: & euery one that beareth fruit, he wil purge it, that it may bring more fruit.

text: not to get the great riches & treasure here in the earth, where the moth and rust shall destroye it, and theues steale it awaye,

text: Loke wherin thou iudgest an other man, thou condemnest thy selfe. in so much that thou that iudgest, doest euen the same.

text: & resurget. A iust man, a good ma falleth.vii. times in a daie, the determinate nomber is put for the vncertaine number.

text: For whosoeuer preacheth any doctrine, not agreable to ye general receiued doctrine in the open knowen church, he it is,

text: For this corruptible body must put on incorruption, and this mortall bodye, must put on immortalitie. Iob xix. chapter.

text: For god commaunded, saying, honour thy father and mother, and who so euer curseth father or mother, shal dye the death.

text: &c. Be you not children lacking discretio, but as a child beareth no malice, so must we beware that we bear no malice:

text: Hee hathe doone all thynges well, he hathe made bothe the deafe to heare, and the du^ to speake. THE EXPOSITION.
