text: Seruauntes obeye your Masters with feare, not onely, if they be good and gentle, but also, if they bee frowarde:
verse_text: Servauntes obey youre masters with all feare not only yf they be good and courteous: but also though they be frowarde.

text: There is yet forty dayes, and Niniue shalbe destroyed, and these wordes that I haue taken to speake of this day:
verse_text: And Ionah began to enter into the citie a dayes iourney, and he cryed, and said, Yet fourtie dayes, and Nineueh shalbe ouerthrowen.

text: This is clere because Christ saith that he that eateth his flesh, and drinketh his blood, hath lyfe euerlasting.
verse_text: He that eateth my flesh, and drinketh my bloud, hath life euerlasting;

text: To the gala, the 5. chapter, the workes of the flesh be manyfest adultry, whordome vncleanesse, wanton nesse &c.
verse_text: And the workes of the flesh be manifest, which are fornication, vncleannes, impudicitie, lecherie,

text: For God sent not his sonne into the world to condemn the worlde, but that the worlde through hym myght be saued.
verse_text: For God sent not his sonne into the worlde to condempne the worlde: but that the worlde through him might be saved.

text: Graecus, non est seruus, neque liber, non est masculus, neque femina, omnes enim vos vnum estis in CHRISTO IESV.
verse_text: Qui enim in Domino vocatus est servus, libertus est Domini: similiter qui liber vocatus est, servus est Christi.

text: Christe is made vnto vs (sayth sainct Paule) wysedome from God and righteousnes, and sanctifiyng, and redempcio.
verse_text: And of him you are in Christ IESVS, who is made vnto vs wisedom from God, & iustice, sanctification, and redemption:

text: Cum non cognouerit mundus per sapientiam deum, placuit deo per stultitiam predicationis saluos facere Credentes.
verse_text: Commonere autem vos volo, scientes semel omnia, quoniam Jesus populum de terra AEgypti salvans, secundo eos, qui non crediderunt, perdidit:

text: Nisi abundauerit iustitia vestra plus quam Scribarum et Phariseorum, non intrabi tis in regnum celorum. Math. 5.
verse_text: vos autem non egrediemini fores tabernaculi, alioquin peribitis: oleum quippe sanctae unctionis est super vos. Qui fecerunt omnia juxta praeceptum Moysi.

text: Yf I haue tolde you earthly thinges, and yet beleue not, how shall you beleue if I tell you of heauenly thynges?
verse_text: If I haue tolde you earthly things, and ye beleeue not: how shall ye beleeue if I tell you of heauenly things?

text: Secondarily, Christ proueth with a playne example, that ye Iews did greuously blaspheme and slaudre him, saying:
verse_text: and he exprobated their incredulity and hardnes of hart, because they did not beleeue them that had seen him risen againe.

text: Ioseph fili Dauid, noli timere accipere Mariam coniugem tuam, quod enim in ea natum est, de spiritu sancto est.
verse_text: dixit ei angelus: Noli timere dare eam isti, quoniam huic timenti Deum debetur conjux filia tua: propterea alius non potuit habere illam.

text: For yt scrip ture came neuer by the wil of man, butholy men of God spake, as they were moued by the holy ghost.
verse_text: For the scripture came never by the will of man: but holy men of god spake as they were moved by the holy goost.

text: Then the deuel toke hym vp vnto the holy city, and setteth him on a pinacle of the temple, and saieth vnto him:
verse_text: Then the deuill taketh him vp into the holy Citie, and setteth him on a pinacle of the Temple,

text: I will send a hunger into the earth, not a hunger for bread, but a hunger for hearing of the word of the lorde.
verse_text: Beholde, the dayes come, sayeth the Lord God, that I will send a famine in the lande, not a famine of bread, nor a thirst for water, but of hearing the word of the Lord.

text: Vequi consurgitis mane ad comessandum, ad Ebrietatem sectandam, et potan do usque aduesperam, ut uino estuetis.
verse_text: foenumque ex agris ad pascenda jumenta, et ut ipsi comedatis ac saturemini.

text: Pontifex appellatus a deo. Pontifex sanctus, innocens, impollutus, segregatus a peccatoribus, excelsior coelis.
verse_text: Pontifex, id est, sacerdos maximus inter fratres suos, super cujus caput fusum est unctionis oleum, et cujus manus in sacerdotio consecratae sunt, vestitusque est sanctis vestibus, caput suum non discooperiet, vestimenta non scindet:

text: The daies of man are but as grasse, he doeth florishe for a litle season euen as it were a flowre in the felde.
verse_text: man, his daies are as grasse, as the floure of the filde so shal he florish.

text: His owne iniquities taketh the wicked persone, and wyth the ropes of his owne sinnes he shalbe strayned & knit.
verse_text: His owne iniquities shall take the wicked himselfe, and he shall be holden with the coards of his sinnes.

text: For ye scripture came neuer by the wil of man, but holy men of God spake, as they were moued by the holi ghost.
verse_text: For the scripture came never by the will of man: but holy men of god spake as they were moved by the holy goost.

text: That is to saye. Who soeuer shall confesse, that Iesus is the sonne of God, in him dwelleth God, and he in God.
verse_text: Whosoeuer shall confesse that Iesus is the Sonne of God, God dwelleth in him, and he in God.

text: Chapter, I liue (saith the Lorde) I wyll not the death of a synner, but that he should be conuerted and line.i.
verse_text: For I desire not the death of him that dyeth, sayth the Lord God: cause therefore one another to returne, and liue ye.

text: Nisi manducaueritis. &c except you eate the flesh of a man, and drink his bloud, you shall haue no life in you.
verse_text: Amen, amen I say to you, Vnles you eate the flesh of the Sonne of man, and drinke his bloud, you shal not haue life in you.

text: And yet not withstanding they did not eat Christs body nor drink his bluod really, putting the in to the mouth:
verse_text: Only beware of this, that thou eat not the blood, for the blood is for the soul: and therefore thou must not eat the soul with the flesh:

text: yf a lyon rore the beastes quake, but we are worsse the beastes, which quake nothing at the roring of the lion,
verse_text: Like as the lyon and the yong lyon roaring on his pray, when a multitude of shepheards is called foorth against him, he will not be afraid of their voice, nor abase himselfe for the noyse of them:

text: Mathew. xxvi. When he said: Poore men ye shal haue alwayes with you, but me shall ye not alwayes haue with you.
verse_text: For the poore you haue alwayes with you: but me you haue not alwayes.

text: whiche entereth into the mouthe defileth the man, but that, whiche commeth out of the mouthe, defileth the man.
verse_text: That which goeth into the mouth, defileth not the man, but that which commeth out of the mouth, that defileth the man.

text: Brother, let me pull out ye mote that is in thine eye, when thou seest not the beame that is in thine owne eie?
verse_text: Either howe canst thou say to thy brother, Brother, let me pull out the mote that is in thine eye, when thou seest not the beame that is in thine owne eye?

text: The gate is larg, and the way is broad that leadeth to perdition, and many there be that entreth into the same.
verse_text: because brode is the gate, and large is the way that leadeth to perdition, and many there be that enter by it.

text: It is better for thee to entre into life with one eye, rather then (hauyng two eyes) to be cast in to hel fyre.
verse_text: It is good for thee hauing one eye to enter into life, rather then hauing two eyes to be cast into the Hel of fire.

text: For I say vnto you, that in heauen their Angels do alwayes be holde the face of my father, whiche is in heauen.
verse_text: for I say to you, that their Angels in Heauen alwaies do see the face of my Father which is in Heauen.

text: Then Simon Peter hauynge a sworde, drewe it, and smote the high priestes seruaunt, and cutte of his right eare.
verse_text: And one of them that stoode by, drewe out a sword, and smote a seruant of the hie Priest, and cut off his eare.

text: &c. Verely verely, I say vnto you, you shall wepe and lament, but the world shal reioyse, and ye shall be sory.
verse_text: Amen, amen I say to you, that you shal weepe and lament, but the world shal reioyce:

text: Nisi abundauerit iustitia vestra plusquam Sribarum et Phariseorum non intrabitis in regnum celorum. Mathee. 5.
verse_text: vos autem non egrediemini fores tabernaculi, alioquin peribitis: oleum quippe sanctae unctionis est super vos. Qui fecerunt omnia juxta praeceptum Moysi.

text: For itt foloweth in the former lettre Qui cum malediceretur, non maledicebat: cum pateretur, non comminabatur.
verse_text: hic autem cum jurejurando per eum, qui dixit ad illum: Juravit Dominus, et non poenitebit eum: tu es sacerdos in aeternum):

text: Ex corde exeunt cogitationes malae, homicidia, adulteria, fornicationes, surta, falsa testimonia, blasphemiae,
verse_text: Ab intus enim de corde hominum malae cogitationes procedunt, adulteria, fornicationes, homicidia,

text: Qui secundum misericordiam suam magnam regenerauit nos in spem viua per resurrectione Iesu christi ex mortuis.
verse_text: qui praedestinatus est Filius Dei in virtute secundum spiritum sanctificationis ex resurrectione mortuorum Jesu Christi Domini nostri:

text: And some saye agayne, that by the vertue and power of Belzebub the prince of diuels, he casteth out the diuel.
verse_text: And the Scribes which were come downe from Hierusalem, said: That he hath Beelzebub; and that in the Prince of Diuels he casteth out Diuels.

text: And her neighbours & cousins herd, how the lord had shewed his great mercie vpon her & they reioysed with her.
verse_text: And her neighbours and her cousins heard how the Lord had shewed great mercy vpon her, and they reioyced with her.

text: wo be to you Scribes and Phariseis, Hypocrites, for you deuoure Widowes houses, vnder coloure of long praiers:
verse_text: Woe to you Scribes and Pharisees, Hypocrites: because you deuoure widowes houses, praying long prayers. For this you shal receaue the greater iudgement.

text: There was a certeyne Riche man, whiche was clothed in purple and fyne whyte, and fared deliciously euery daie.
verse_text: Ther was a certayne ryche man which was clothed in purple and fyne bysse and fared deliciously every daye.

text: But the people that saw it, meruailed and gloryfied God, which had giuen suche power vnto men. THE EXPOSITION.
verse_text: And the multitudes seeing it, were afrayd, and glorified God that gaue such power to men.

text: Omnis turba qui simul aderat ad spectaculu istud & uidebat quae fiebat, percutientes pectora sua reuertebatur.
verse_text: Ingredientesque ad regem, quidquid postulassent ad ornatum pertinens, accipiebant: et ut eis placuerat, compositae de triclinio feminarum ad regis cubiculum transibant.

text: O thou full of all craft, and guile, enemie to al iustice, thou ceasest not to destroy the right waies of God:
verse_text: And said, O full of all subtilty and all mischiefe, thou child of the deuil, thou enemie of all righteousnesse, wilt thou not cease to peruert the right wayes of the Lord?

text: That is to saye Who soeuer shall confesse, that Iesus is the sonne of God, in him dwelleth God, and he in God.
verse_text: Whosoeuer shall confesse that Iesus is the Sonne of God, God dwelleth in him, and he in God.

text: That he knewe nothing, but Christ, and that he was crucified. And to the Gal. God forbid that I shuld reioyse,
verse_text: God forbyd that I shuld reioyce but in the crosse of oure Lorde Iesu Christ wherby the worlde is crucified as touchinge me and I as concerninge the worlde.

text: Cor. vi. Be not deceaued, for neither fornicatours, neither aduoutrers shall inherite the kyngdome of heauen.
verse_text: Know you not that the vniust shal not possesse the Kingdom of God? Doe not erre: Neither fornicatours, nor seruers of Idols, nor aduouterers, nor the effeminate, nor the liers with mankind,

text: He hath inclined the heaues, and came downe and trode darkenes, that is to say, sinne, downe vnder his feete.
verse_text: He bowed the heauens also and came downe, and darkenes was vnder his feete.

text: He is that dearely beloued sonne, for whose sake, god is fully pacified, satisfied and sette at one with man.
verse_text: For he receiued of God the Father honour and glory, when there came such a voyce to him from that excellent glory, This is my beloued Sonne, in whom I am well pleased.

text: Nolite de cuncta substantia vestra fraudare decimam, ne vobis nouem partes auferantur & sola decima remaneat.
verse_text: Si remittitis arcam Dei Israel, nolite dimittere eam vacuam, sed quod debetis, reddite ei pro peccato, et tunc curabimini:

text: The brother that is holpe of hys brother is as a sure and wel fenced city, and a strong Tower he is so strog.
verse_text: He that possesseth a good wife, beginneth a possession: she is a help like to himself, and a pillar of rest.

text: Therfore shal ma forsake father and mother, and kepe himself vnto his wyfe, and thei shalbe two in one flesh.
verse_text: For this cause, man shal leaue father & mother, & shal cleaue to his wife, and they two shal be in one flesh.

text: For it is thanke worthy, if a man for conscience towarde God, suffereth grief, and suffreth wroge vndeserued:
verse_text: For it is thankeworthye yf a man for conscience towarde god endure grefe sufferinge wrongfully.

text: the fathers that haue eaten Manna be deade, but he that eateth this bread dyeth not, but shall lyue for euer.
verse_text: This is the bread that came downe from Heauen. Not as your Fathers did eate Manna, and died. He that eateth this bread, shal liue for euer.

text: When they consider your holye conuersation (sayth saint Peter) with louing feare of God and of your husbands.
verse_text: While they beholde your pure conuersation, which is with feare.

text: And agayne strayet is the dore and the way narrow which leadeth into heauen, and fewe there be that fynde it.
verse_text: But strayte is the gate and narowe ys the waye which leadeth vnto lyfe: and feawe there be that fynde it.

text: Are they not al ministring spirites, sent to minister for theire sakes which shalbe the heires of saluacion?
verse_text: Are they not al, ministring spirits: sent to minister for them which shal receiue the inheritance of saluation?

text: Nolineg ligere gratiam quae in te est, quae data est tibi per prophetiam cum impositione manuum presbiterii.
verse_text: Propter quam causam admoneo te ut resuscites gratiam Dei, quae est in te per impositionem manuum mearum.

text: He called them Hipocrites, and bad them shewe him the coyne or money that was vsually payde for the tribute.
verse_text: Then the high Priest tolde him that there was such money layde vp for the reliefe of widowes, and fatherlesse children,

text: & hath tryumphed ouer them in his own person, wt which words Paul writeth y christ did triumph on ye crosse.
verse_text: And that he might reconcile both vnto God in one body by his crosse, and slay hatred thereby,

text: Cayphas was he, which gaue councel to the Iewes that it was expedient, that one ma shuld dye for the people.
verse_text: Cayphas was he that gave counsell to the Iewes that it was expediet that one man shuld dye for the people.

text: And Christ also: Nowe is come the iudgement of this worlde, and the prince of this worlde shalbe thrust out.
verse_text: Now is the iudgement of this worlde: now shall the prince of this worlde be cast out.

text: And then howe all these seuen giftes presuppo^eth faith, hope, and charitie, in him that shall receiue them.
verse_text: it is a token of the certeintie, for that the worde of God shal come to passe, and be fulfilled spedely.

text: and said, for this cause shal man leaue father & mother and cleaue to his wyfe & they two shalbe one fleshe?
verse_text: For this cause, man shal leaue father & mother, & shal cleaue to his wife, and they two shal be in one flesh.

text: Sacrilege, murder, adultery, false witnes, thefte, rape, pride, enuy, auarice, anger, if it continue in man,
verse_text: thefts, auarices, wickednesse, guile, impudicities, an euil eye, blasphemie, pride, foolishnes.

text: To what purpose were it to work this most great miracle, that it should not be seen, when it were ones done?
verse_text: But that to deceive them who had trusted to the place and temple which is honoured throughout the whole world, for the reverence and holiness of it, was a thing which could not by any means be done.

text: Uerily I say vnto you, onles ye turne, and become as children, ye shal not entre into the kingdom of heauen.
verse_text: Amen I say to you, vnless you be converted, and become as litle children, you shal not enter into the Kingdom of Heauen.

text: And agayne he sayeth: Christ did dye, and rose agayne, because he should be Lord, both of the dead & quicke.
verse_text: For Christ therfore dyed and rose agayne and revived that he myght be lorde both of deed and quicke.

text: The peace of god, whyche exceedeth all vnderstanding, mought keepe your heartes and myndes, in Christe Iesu.
verse_text: And the peace of god which passeth all vnderstondinge kepe youre hertes and myndes in christ Iesu.

text: Paule sayth: Vt i^stitia legis impleretur in nobis, qui non secundum carnem versamur, sed secundum spiritum.
verse_text: Nunc autem soluti sumus a lege mortis, in qua detinebamur, ita ut serviamus in novitate spiritus, et non in vetustate litterae.

text: For they (as we do read in the gospel) are blessed that huger and thirst iustice, for they shalbe satisfied.
verse_text: I haue shewed you al things, that so labouring, you must receiue the weake, and remember the word of our Lord IESVS, because he said: It is a more blessed thing to giue rather then to take.

text: and all acquaintance: is not he for these thinges in great honour with al men, and with god in great glorie?
verse_text: Vexed in few thinges, in many they shal be wel disposed of: because God hath tempted them, and hath found them worthie of him selfe.

text: Yf a man kepe my saying he shal neuer tast of death Act thou greater then our father Abraham which is dead?
verse_text: The Iewes therfore said: Now we haue knowen that thou hast a Diuel. Abraham is dead, and the Prophets; and thou saiest: If any man keep my word, he shal not tast death for euer.

text: Or els shall they bee found at Ierusalem, where so great a company of honest Scribes & Phariseis are found?
verse_text: Take heed of the Scribes that wil walke in long robes, and be saluted in the market-place,

text: For in this zeale, our Lorde Iesus Christ did driue with a whippe, the biars and sellers out of the temple.
verse_text: AND the people seeing that Moyses made tariance ere he came downe from the mount, being assembled against Aaron, they sayd:

text: So then, when the Lorde had spoken vnto them he was receiued into heauen, and is on the right hande of God.
verse_text: So then when the lorde had spoken vnto them he was receaued into heauen and is set doune on the ryght honde of God.

text: Viri diligite vxores vestras, sicut christus dilexit sponsam suam ecclesiam, et semetipsum tradidit pro ea.
verse_text: et ambulate in dilectione, sicut et Christus dilexit nos, et tradidit semetipsum pro nobis, oblationem et hostiam Deo in odorem suavitatis.

text: Christ saith: what thincke ye of within your selues, o me of litle faith, that you haue not brought breade?
verse_text: And IESVS knowing it, said why do you thinke within your selues, O ye of litle faith, for that your haue not bread?

text: & Niniue subuertitur. yet fortye dayes & Niniue subuertitur, and Niniue shall be destroied, it was no more.
verse_text: And Ionah began to enter into the citie a dayes iourney, and he cryed, and said, Yet fourtie dayes, and Nineueh shalbe ouerthrowen.

text: and sayth: Fyrst seeke the kingdom of god and his righteousnes, and al these thinges shalbe geuen vnto you.
verse_text: Seeke therefore first the Kingdom of God, and the iustice of him, and al these things shal be giuen you besides.

text: He that asketh, shall haue, and he that seketh, shal find, and he that knocketh, shall haue the doore open.
verse_text: For euery one that asketh, receiueth: and he that seeketh, findeth: and to him that knocketh, it shal be opened.

text: Christus pro nobis mortuus est, in cuius sanguine iustificati sumus, in cuius sanguine salui erimus ab ira.
verse_text: Res Spiritus oris nostri, christus Dominus, captus est in peccatis nostris, cui diximus: In umbra tua vivemus in gentibus.

text: For Christes death is so perfect a sacrifice, yt by ye one offering we are made cleane from sinne for euer.
verse_text: which hath not necessitie daily (as the Priestes) first for his owne sinnes to offer Hostes, then for the peoples. For this he did once, in offering himself.

text: And it is sayde more, not that any man hath seen the father, but he that is of God he hath seen the father.
verse_text: Not that eny man hath sene the father save he which is of God:

text: Ne quam vsquam demus offentionem ne reprehendatur ministeriu sed in omnibus comendemus nos ut Dei ministri.
verse_text: Si alii potestatis vestrae participes sunt, quare non potius nos? Sed non usi sumus hac potestate: sed omnia sustinemus, ne quod offendiculum demus Evangelio Christi.

text: Except a manne be borne againe by water and the holye spirite, he cannot entre into the kyngdome of heauen.
verse_text: Iesus answered: verely verely I saye vnto the: except that a man be boren of water and of the sprete he cannot enter into the kyngdome of god.

text: I will be pacified concerning their vnrightuosnes, and their sinnes and iniquities I will no more remember.
verse_text: For I will bee mercifull to their vnrighteousnes, and I wil remember their sinnes and their iniquities no more.

text: The Sunne shall neuer be thy day lyght, (as Esai said) & the lyght of the Moone shall neuer shine vnto the:
verse_text: The Sunne shall be no more thy light by day, neither for brightnesse shall the moone giue light vnto thee:

text: Lassati sumus in via iniquitatis & perditiois, ambul auimus vias difficiles, viam autem domini ignorauimus.
verse_text: flagellum inundans cum transierit, non veniet super nos quia posuimus mendacium spem nostram, et mendacio protecti sumus.

text: and howe the hye priestes and our rulers deliuered him to bee condempned to death, and haue crucified him.
verse_text: And how the hye prestes and oure rulers delyvered him to be condempned to deeth: and have crucified him.

text: Thomas bicause thou hast seen me thou hast beleued, blessed are they y haue not seen and yet haue beleued.
verse_text: Iesus sayde vnto him. Thomas because thou hast sene me therfore thou belevest: Happy are they that have not sene and yet beleve.

text: Take heede & beware of all couetousnes, for a mans life standeth not in the aboundaunce of hys possession.
verse_text: Wherfore he sayde vnto them: take hede and beware of covetousnes. For no mannes lyfe stondeth in the aboundaunce of the thinges which he possesseth.

text: Dedit illi no men quod est super omne nomen vt in nomine Iesu omne genu flectatur, celestium, terrestrium,
verse_text: et non tenens caput, ex quo totum corpus per nexus, et conjunctiones subministratum, et constructum crescit in augmentum Dei.

text: And sainct Paule saith: Those that rule well and faithfully with the word, they are worthye double honour.
verse_text: The elders that rule wel are worthy of double honoure most specially they which laboure in the worde and in teachinge.

text: God, I thanke the, that I am not as other men are, extorsioners, vniust, aduoutrers, or as thys publicane.
verse_text: God, I giue thee thankes that I am not as the rest of men, extorcioners, uniust, aduouterers, as also this Publican.

text: T He was a certaine riche man which was clothed in purple and fine white, and fared deliciously euery day.
verse_text: There was a certaine rich man, & he was clothed with purple and silke: and he fared euery day magnifically.

text: What day so euer thou shalt eate of the tree of knowlege of good and euill, thou shalt surely dye a death.
verse_text: But of the tree of knowledge of good and euill, thou shalt not eate of it: for in the day that thou eatest thereof, thou shalt die the death.

text: Uerely I say vnto you, inasmuche as ye haue done it vnto one of ye least of these, ye haue done it to me.
verse_text: Then shall he answere them, saying, Uerely, I say vnto you, in as much as ye did it not to one of the least of these, ye did it not to me.

text: Christ rose agayne, and appeared vnto his Apostles, declaryng by many myracles, that he had verely rysen,
verse_text: Iohn Baptiste is rysen agayne from deeth and therfore miracles are wrought by him.

text: We are debtors to the fleshe, not that wee should liue after the fleshe, for if ye liue after the fleshe,
verse_text: Therefore brethren, wee are detters not to the flesh, to liue after the flesh:

text: And foloweth there, Non poterat ibi vertutem vlla facere, nisi paucos infirmos impositis manibus curauit.

verse_text: Amen dico vobis, quia sunt quidam de hic stantibus, qui non gustabunt mortem donec videant regnum Dei veniens in virtute.

text: We haue sinned, we haue don wicked ly, we haue behaued our selues vngodly, in all thy rightousnes.
verse_text: For we haue sinned, and done vnjustly reuolting from thee: and we haue offended in al thinges;

text: Mortify (saith he) your earthly mebres, fornication, vncleanes, vnnatural lust, euel cocupiscence,
verse_text: For the time past sufficeth (to accomplish the wil of the Gentils) them that haue walked in riotousnes, desires, excesse of wine, banketings, potations, and vnlawful seruices of Idols.

text: Beatus es Simon Bariona, quia caro & sanguis non reuelauit tibi, sed pater meus qui in coelis est.
verse_text: et descendit Spiritus Sanctus corporali specie sicut columba in ipsum: et vox de caelo facta est: Tu es filius meus dilectus, in te complacui mihi.

text: Iesus aunswered: Thou couldest haue no power at all against me, except it were geue the fro aboue.
verse_text: Iesus answered, Thou couldest haue no power at all against me, except it were giuen thee from aboue:

text: Let vs confesse with our mouth & beleue with our harte that God raised Christe from death to life,
verse_text: For yf thou shalt knowledge with thy mouth that Iesus is the lorde and shalt beleve with thyn hert that God raysed him up from deeth thou shalt be safe.

text: AD quem accedentes lapidem viuum ab hominibus quide reprobatu a deo autem electum & honorificatum.
verse_text: Ecce ego mittam in fundamentis Sion lapidem, lapidem probatum, angularem, pretiosum, in fundamento fundatum;

text: Roma. 5. So that grace shold reigne by righteousnes to euerlasting life by Iesu Christ. Ro.vi. ch.
verse_text: filled with the frutes of rightewesnes which frutes come by Iesus Christ vnto the glory and laude of God.

text: Geue therfore vnto Cesar, the thinges which are Cesars, and vnto god those thinges that are godes.
verse_text: Then sayd he vnto them, Giue therefore to Cesar, the things which are Cesars, and giue vnto God, those things which are Gods.

text: Nay not so (saith god) but thou shalt be cast downe to the bottom of the lake, or dungeon of hell.
verse_text: But yet thou shalt be brought down to hell, into the depth of the pit.

text: Euen therwith, bicause that he was exalted on the crosse, like as the serpent was in ye wildernes.
verse_text: that serue the exampler and shadow of heauenly things. As it was answered Moyses, when he finished the tabernacle, See (quoth he) that thou make al things according to the exampler which was shewed thee in the mount.

text: to him the porter openeth, and the shepe heare hys voyce, and hee calleth hys owne sheepe by name,

text: Giue this man place. But when thou art called, set the doune in the lowest place, that he may say:
verse_text: But when thou art bidden, goe and sit downe in the lowest roome, that when he that bade thee, cometh, he may say vnto thee, Friende, sit vp hier:

text: And ye shall beare witnes also, bicause ye haue beene with me from the beginninge. THE EXPOSITION.
verse_text: And ye also shall beare witnesse, because ye haue bene with me from the beginning.

text: And that they do good, and be rich in good workes, and liberall in geuing and dealing theyr goods.
verse_text: that they which beleeue in God, be careful to excel in good workes.

text: Truly when Iudas, not the Iscariot, according to this saiyng, did aske Christ in his laste supper:
verse_text: And when supper was done, whereas the Diuel now had put into the hart of Iudas Iscariote the sonne of Simon, to betray him:

text: Fourthly S. Iohn putteth a difference betwene his baptisme & the baptisme of Christ, whe he saith:
verse_text: beginning from the Baptisme of Iohn vntil the day wherein he was assumpted from vs, there must one of these be made a witnes with vs of his resurrection.

text: The breade which I shal giue vnto you, is my fleshe, whiche I shal giue for the lyfe of the world.
verse_text: and the bread that I will giue, is my flesh, which I will giue for the life of the world.

text: & delyuering vs fro the power of darkenes, hath ledde vs into the kingedome of his beloued sonne:
verse_text: Which hath delivered vs from the power of dercknes and hath translated vs in to the kyngdome of his dere sone

text: Except you eate the fleshe of the sonne of man, and drink his bloud, ye shal haue no life in you.
verse_text: Amen, amen I say to you, Vnles you eate the flesh of the Sonne of man, and drinke his bloud, you shal not haue life in you.

text: Except ye eate the fleshe of the sonne of man, and drynke his blood, you can haue no lyfe in you.
verse_text: Verely, verely I saye vnto you except ye eate the flesshe of the sonne of man and drinke his bloude ye shall not have lyfe in you.

text: Curam habe de bono nomine, hoc enim magis permanebit tibi quam mille thesauri preciosi et magni :
verse_text: Melius est parum cum timore Domini, quam thesauri magni et insatiabiles.

text: & for the name of our lord Iesu Christ vt idipsum dicatis omnes, et non sint in vobis scismata.i.
verse_text: Denuntiamus autem vobis, fratres, in nomine Domini nostri Jesu Christi, ut subtrahatis vos ab omni fratre ambulante inordinate, et non secundum traditionem, quam acceperunt a nobis.

text: I am a worme and not a man a laughing stocke or an obprobrie of men and the refuse of the people.
verse_text: But I am a worme and no man: a reproch of men and outcast of the people.

text: Ananias, how is it that satha hath filled thy harte, that thou shouldest lye vnto the holy ghost?
verse_text: Ananias, why hath Satan tempted thy hart, that thou shouldest lie to the Holy Ghost, and defraud of the price of the land?

text: Math. v. Beati qui persecutionem patiuntur propter iusticiam, quoniam ipsorum est regnum celorum.
verse_text: Beati pauperes spiritu: quoniam ipsorum est regnum caelorum.

verse_text: When Herod the king had heard these things, he was troubled, and all Hierusalem with him.

verse_text: But Thomas one of the twelve called Didymus was not with the when Iesus came.

verse_text: So then I my silfe in my mynde serve the lawe of God and in my flesshe the lawe of synne.

text: Then came Iesus when the doores were shut, and stoode in the middes, and sayd: Peace be vnto you.
verse_text: Then came Iesus, when the doores were shut, and stood in the middes, and said, Peace be vnto you.

text: For herein is the worde true, that there is one that soweth and P A G Exli an other that reapeth.
verse_text: For in this is the saying true: that it is one man that soweth, and it is another that reapeth.

text: Father Abraha, haue mercy on me, and send Lazarus, that he may dip the typ of hi finger in water,
verse_text: And he cried, and said, Father Abraham, haue mercy on mee, and send Lazarus, that he may dip the tip of his finger in water, and coole my tongue, for I am tormented in this flame.

text: But Christ did speake of his death but they thought that he had spoken of the sleaping of sleape.
verse_text: Howbeit Iesus spake of his death: but they thought that hee had spoken of taking of rest in sleepe.

text: that the triall and proofe of your faythe much more precious then golde that is tryed by the fyre
verse_text: that youre fayth once tried beinge moche more precious then golde that perissheth (though it be tried with fyre) myght be founde vnto lawde glory and honoure at the apperinge of Iesus Christ:

text: Yet a litle while, and the worlde seeth me no more, but ye se me, for I lyue, and you shall lyue.
verse_text: Yet a litle while, and the world seeth me no more: but ye see me, because I liue, ye shall liue also.

text: Qui administrat semen seminanti, et pauem ad manducandum prestabit & multiplicabit semen vestrum,

text: A people whome I haue not knowen, shall serue me, as soone as they hear of me, they shal obey me,
verse_text: Strangers shalbe in subiection to me: assoone as they heare, they shall obey me.

text: To this saint Paule doth exhorte vs, not onely for feare of vengeance, but bycause of conscience.
verse_text: Wherfore ye must nedes obeye not for feare of vengeaunce only: but also because of conscience.

text: He that seketh shall fynde, he that asketh shall obtayne, to hym that knocketh, it shalbe opened.
verse_text: For euery one that asketh, receiueth: and he that seeketh, findeth: and to him that knocketh, it shal be opened.

text: Qui potest saluum facere a morte, offerens preces & supplicationes cum clamore valido & lacrimis,
verse_text: Prosperans enim homo sine querela deprecari pro populis, proferens servitutis suae scutum, orationem et per incensum deprecationem allegans, restitit irae, et finem imposuit necessitati, ostendens quoniam tuus est famulus.

text: It is not for you to knowe the tymes or the seasons, whych the father hath put in hys owne power:
verse_text: It is not for you to knowe the tymes or the seasons which the father hath put in his awne power:

text: Secodarily, Nowe are ye cleane (sayth Christe) because of the worde that I haue spoken vnto you.
verse_text: Why axest thou me? Axe them whiche hearde me what I sayde vnto them. Beholde they can tell what I sayde.

text: Repente lo quar aduersum gente et aduersus regnum, ut eradicem et destruam, et disper dam illud:
verse_text: Et dispergam eos virum a fratre suo, et patres et filios pariter, ait Dominus. Non parcam, et non concedam: neque miserebor, ut non disperdam eos.

text: Hijs quidem qui secundum patientiam boni operis, gloriam & honorem & incorruptione quaerentibus,
verse_text: Magis autem eos, qui post carnem in concupiscentia immunditiae ambulant, dominationemque contemnunt, audaces, sibi placentes, sectas non metuunt introducere blasphemantes:

text: Come ye blessed children, and inherite the kingdome, for I was an hungred, and ye gaue me meate.
verse_text: For I was an hungred, and ye gaue me meate:

text: And I saye vnto the, that thou arte Peter, or a rock, and on this rocke I wyll buylde my church,
verse_text: And I saye also vnto the that thou arte Peter: and apon this rocke I wyll bylde my congregacion. And the gates of hell shall not prevayle ageynst it.

verse_text: Mementote qualiter salvi facti sunt patres nostri in mari Rubro, cum sequeretur eos Pharao cum exercitu multo.

text: Ibant gaudentes a cospectu consilii quoniam digni habiti sunt pro nomine Ihesu contumeliam pati.

verse_text: Ubi multae sunt opes, multi et qui comedunt eas. Et quid prodest possessori, nisi quod cernit divitias oculis suis?

verse_text: And hee that requiteth good turnes, is mindfull of that which may come heereafter: and when he falleth he shall find a stay.

text: For he is made vnto vs wisedome from God, and righteousnes, and sanctificacion, and redempcion.

text: But yet (sayth Christ) blessed and happy be the mercyfull, for they shall agayne receyue mercy.

text: So that you first knowe this, that no prophecy in ye scripture hath any priuate interpretation,

text: & not by the workes of the lawe, because that no man shalbe iustified by the workes of the law.

verse_text: All even as many as came before me are theves and robbers: but the shepe dyd not heare them.

verse_text: No, father Abraham, but if some man shal goe from the dead to them, they wil doe penance.

verse_text: pray therefore the Lord of the haruest to sende foorth labourers into his haruest.

text: and a fleshly man can vnderstand nothing but fleshly things, and cannot perceaue godly thinges.
verse_text: For all things cannot be in men, because the son of man is not immortal, and they are delighted with the vanity of evil.

verse_text: And when they came that were hired about the eleuenth houre, they receiued euery man a penie.

verse_text: And it shall come to passe, that whosoeuer shall call on the Name of the Lord, shalbe saued.

text: There is nothing stronger then it, and therefore charitie is compared vnto the strength of it.
verse_text: for she teacheth sobrietie, and prudence, and iustice, and strength, then the which nothing is more profitable in life to men.

verse_text: Soche an hye prest it became vs to have which is wholy harmlesse vndefyled separat from synners and made hyar then heven.

verse_text: prohibentium nubere, abstinere a cibis, quod Deus creavit ad percipiendum cum gratiarum actione fidelibus, et iis qui cognoverunt veritatem.

text: He bringeth forth a yong tree that may geue shadow to Ionas, wherof Ionas reioyceth very much.
verse_text: And our Lord God perpared an iuie tree, & it came vp ouer the head of Ionas, to be a shadow ouer his head, and to couer him: for he had laboured: and Ionas reioyced vpon the iuie with great ioy.

text: In that that he suffred and was tempted, he is able to helpe them that be tempted or troubled.
verse_text: For in that he himselfe hath suffered, being tempted, he is able to succour them that are tempted.

text: For how can he that loueth not his brother whome he hath sene, loue God whom he hath not sene?
verse_text: For he that loueth not his brother whom he seeth, God whom he seeth not, how can he loue?

text: Quiuos audit me audit & qui uos *, me spernit. Qui autem me spernit, spernit eum qui misit me.
verse_text: Amen, amen dico vobis: qui accipit si quem misero, me accipit; qui autem me accipit, accipit eum qui me misit.

text: Ihon saith: hereby manifestly are knowen the children of God, from the chyldren of the deuill:
verse_text: In this the children of God are manifest, and the children of the deuill:

text: Except ye wheat corne (saieth Christ) fal into ye ground and dye, it bringeth forthe no fruit.
verse_text: Amen, amen I say to you, vnles the graine of wheate falling into the ground, die: it self remaineth alone. but if it die, it bringeth much fruit.

text: That whych is borne of the flesh, is flesh, and that which is borne of the spirite is spirite.
verse_text: That which is borne of the flesh, is flesh, and that which is borne of the spirit, is spirit.

verse_text: So ought men to loue their wiues, as their owne bodies: hee that loueth his wife, loueth himselfe.

text: Christ pronounceth them blessed that hungre and thirste for righteousnes, addyng thys promise:

text: Peace I leaue wyth you, my peace I gyue vnto you, not as the world gyueth, gyue I vnto you &c.
verse_text: Peace I leaue with you, my peace I giue vnto you, not as the world giueth, giue I vnto you:

text: nor heare your preachyng, departe out of that house or citie, and shake the dust of your fete.
verse_text: And howe many so euer will not receiue you, when ye goe out of that citie, shake off the very dust from your feete for a testimonie against them.

text: But I saye vnto you, that whosoeuer is angry with his brother, shalbe in daunger of iudgement.
verse_text: But I say vnto you, that whosoeuer is angry with his brother without a cause, shall be in danger of the Iudgement:

verse_text: For the pistles (sayth he) are sore and stronge: but his bodyly presence is weake and his speache rude.

text: GOD will not heare your prayers, for he is the GOD of peace, and not of discention and debate.
verse_text: God be Iudge betweene vs and you: for you haue done vs great iniury in that you haue not required peace of the children of Assur.

text: I wyll come again, and receiue you euen vnto my selfe, that where I am, there may ye bee also.
verse_text: I come againe and wil take you to my self, that where I am, you also may be.

text: And when he is come, he will rebuke the worlde of sinne, and of righteousnes, and of iugement.
verse_text: And when he is come he will rebuke the worlde of synne and of rightwesnes and of iudgement.

text: Quasi pannus menstruatae omnes iustitiae nostrae, be filthy and ve•y vile in the sight of God.
verse_text: We are esteemed of him as counterfeits: he abstaineth from our wayes as from filthinesse: he pronounceth the end of the iust to be blessed, and maketh his boast that God is his father.

text: saying: Whye tempte ye God, laying the yoke vpon the disciples neckes, which our forefathers,
verse_text: Now therfore why tempte ye God that ye wolde put a yoke on the disciples neckes which nether oure fathers nor we were able to beare.

text: Parati semper ad satisfactionem omni poscenti vos rationem de ea que in vobis est spe & fide.

text: I wold say vnto you,
verse_text: But to you I say: Possess their land which I will give you for an inheritance, a land flowing with milk and honey. I am the Lord your God, who have separated you from other people.

text: And if they so were,
verse_text: And they did so: for Aaron stretched out his hand with his rod, and smote the dust of the earth, and it became lice, in man and in beast: all the dust of the land became lice throughout all the land of Egypt.

text: And now ye know him,
verse_text: Euen the Spirit of trueth, whome the world can not receiue, because it seeth him not, neither knoweth him: but ye knowe him: for he dwelleth with you, and shalbe in you.

text: But I say vnto you.
verse_text: Truly I say vnto you: it shalbe easier for the londe of zodoma and Gomorra in the daye of iudgement then for that cite.

text: And he said to her.
verse_text: and he said to him: To thee wil I giue this whole power, and the glorie of them; for to me they are deliuered, and to whom I wil, I doe giue them.

text: & they sayd to him:
verse_text: And IESVS knew, that they would aske him; & he said to them: Of this you doe question among your selues, because I said to you: A litle while, and you shal not see me; and againe a litle while, and you shal see me.

text: To this I tell the,
verse_text: And I will bring the third part through the fire, and will refine them as silver is refined: and I will try them as gold is tried. They shall call on my name, and I will hear them. I will say: Thou art my people: and they shall say: The Lord is my God.
